1
00:00:00,021 --> 00:00:02,561
The most entertaining suspense
that predicts love.

2
00:00:02,561 --> 00:00:04,481
Love line prediction game, Heart Signal.

3
00:00:04,481 --> 00:00:08,381
Five people with sharp romance
radars have gathered.

4
00:00:08,381 --> 00:00:10,551
[The panel of five people is here]

5
00:00:10,551 --> 00:00:12,891
The panel failed to predict the last time.

6
00:00:12,891 --> 00:00:14,141
- That's right.
- A total failure.

7
00:00:14,141 --> 00:00:16,881
- How could we have?
- It was impossible.

8
00:00:16,881 --> 00:00:22,451
We can no longer introduce
ourselves as sharp radars.

9
00:00:22,451 --> 00:00:25,631
- No, Eana. You still got it.
- But...

10
00:00:25,631 --> 00:00:30,361
I'm only half sharp. I'm half dull now.

11
00:00:30,361 --> 00:00:33,501
It's not our fault. It's those kids' fault.

12
00:00:33,501 --> 00:00:34,781
[Those kids?]

13
00:00:34,781 --> 00:00:37,981
But it proves that they're honest.

14
00:00:37,981 --> 00:00:40,981
They have certain feelings,

15
00:00:40,981 --> 00:00:43,441
but they're making different decisions.

16
00:00:43,441 --> 00:00:45,311
That's how it is in real life.

17
00:00:45,311 --> 00:00:48,221
- The lint roller worked.
- Good job, lint roller.

18
00:00:48,221 --> 00:00:49,681
How could we have guessed that?

19
00:00:49,681 --> 00:00:53,081
And they signaled a lot of disappointment.

20
00:00:53,081 --> 00:00:55,521
That's how sincere they are.

21
00:00:55,521 --> 00:00:59,671
- That's why we were so confused.
- So hard.

22
00:00:59,671 --> 00:01:03,621
Everyone went to Yeongjongdo for
their first weekend in the Signal House.

23
00:01:03,621 --> 00:01:07,121
The love lines got chaotic there.

24
00:01:07,121 --> 00:01:09,411
It was crazy.

25
00:01:09,411 --> 00:01:12,351
I guess you can speed your way into love.

26
00:01:12,351 --> 00:01:16,401
They get anxious
because they're falling so fast.

27
00:01:16,401 --> 00:01:18,881
You just have to enjoy the moment
when you're in love.

28
00:01:18,881 --> 00:01:21,451
- It's not easy.
- It really isn't.

29
00:01:21,451 --> 00:01:24,711
When I was younger,
I was honest with my feelings.

30
00:01:24,711 --> 00:01:28,171
But everything has worked out for you.

31
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:29,721
[I didn't know. I see...]

32
00:01:29,721 --> 00:01:31,611
I see.

33
00:01:31,611 --> 00:01:33,701
I guess so.

34
00:01:33,701 --> 00:01:35,821
I didn't know, but I was like that, too.

35
00:01:35,821 --> 00:01:39,741
Yu Gyeong struggled a lot because
Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri got close.

36
00:01:39,741 --> 00:01:41,641
I felt so bad for her.

37
00:01:41,641 --> 00:01:44,061
I understand how she must've felt.

38
00:01:44,061 --> 00:01:48,691
She got confused since she thought
Wu Yeol texted her.

39
00:01:48,691 --> 00:01:51,421
Min Ju got upset since
Seong Min helped Yu Gyeong.

40
00:01:51,421 --> 00:01:53,431
Gosh, what a mess.

41
00:01:53,431 --> 00:01:55,421
Complete chaos in Yeongjongdo.

42
00:01:55,421 --> 00:01:57,731
What a mess. Never going back to Yeongjongdo.

43
00:01:57,731 --> 00:01:59,471
You aren't going back?

44
00:01:59,471 --> 00:02:04,671
When they got home, the women
chose their first official date.

45
00:02:04,671 --> 00:02:08,041
They chose a book that the men brought.

46
00:02:08,041 --> 00:02:10,411
They'll go on a date
with the owner of the book.

47
00:02:10,411 --> 00:02:14,551
Everyone chose based on Gyu Ri's guess.

48
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:16,261
I think she was totally wrong.

49
00:02:16,261 --> 00:02:17,661
- I agree.
- Right?

50
00:02:17,661 --> 00:02:19,241
- All wrong.
- You're saying...

51
00:02:19,241 --> 00:02:20,941
[Quickly changing her mind]

52
00:02:20,941 --> 00:02:22,761
Gosh, my crappy radar.

53
00:02:22,761 --> 00:02:27,151
If she ends up with Seo Won by mistake,

54
00:02:27,151 --> 00:02:30,781
something might happen
because he was her first crush.

55
00:02:30,781 --> 00:02:33,161
- She liked him in the beginning.
- Right.

56
00:02:33,161 --> 00:02:36,191
They didn't go with their first impressions.

57
00:02:36,191 --> 00:02:39,141
Gosh, this is so hard.

58
00:02:39,141 --> 00:02:42,991
[It's the day of their first official date]

59
00:02:43,501 --> 00:02:46,551
I was really nervous.

60
00:02:46,551 --> 00:02:50,441
Excitement? There was a bit of that.

61
00:02:52,701 --> 00:02:56,611
[Getting ready to go out, feeling excited]

62
00:03:00,131 --> 00:03:02,441
[Tap, tap]

63
00:03:02,441 --> 00:03:04,771
My heart feels a bit ticklish.

64
00:03:04,771 --> 00:03:08,911
Who will it be? I have no idea.

65
00:03:08,911 --> 00:03:11,021
I was excited without realizing.

66
00:03:11,021 --> 00:03:13,221
[Will I see the person I wanted to see?]

67
00:03:16,311 --> 00:03:18,631
I couldn't help but smile.

68
00:03:19,581 --> 00:03:23,341
- That's when I started believing in fate.
- What?

69
00:03:23,341 --> 00:03:27,261
I can't forget how she looked from behind.

70
00:03:27,261 --> 00:03:29,171
Hello.

71
00:03:29,171 --> 00:03:33,551
[Their first date can be a new start]

72
00:03:36,411 --> 00:03:39,271
[What will happen on today's dates?]

73
00:03:39,271 --> 00:03:44,791
[The evening of Day 4]

74
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:45,971
[Holding a book]

75
00:03:45,971 --> 00:03:48,001
"On Love"?

76
00:03:48,001 --> 00:03:50,741
[Gyu Ri is holding a book,
waiting for someone]

77
00:03:50,741 --> 00:03:53,711
Gyu Ri is hoping for Wu Yeol.

78
00:03:53,711 --> 00:03:57,961
I want to talk to the person
who read this book.

79
00:03:57,961 --> 00:03:59,941
Can you guess, Unni?

80
00:03:59,941 --> 00:04:02,231
This is Wu Yeol's, I think.

81
00:04:02,231 --> 00:04:04,661
Is that your hunch?

82
00:04:04,661 --> 00:04:05,571
[Studying]

83
00:04:05,571 --> 00:04:08,501
I wanted to have a date with Wu Yeol.

84
00:04:08,501 --> 00:04:12,751
I thought I could confirm the feelings.

85
00:04:12,751 --> 00:04:15,701
See? She cried yesterday,
but she still wants him.

86
00:04:15,701 --> 00:04:18,281
It's because she likes him too much.

87
00:04:18,281 --> 00:04:23,311
[Could the owner of the book be him?]

88
00:04:23,311 --> 00:04:24,491
[Someone is approaching her]

89
00:04:24,491 --> 00:04:26,541
- Huh?
- Wu Yeol?

90
00:04:30,961 --> 00:04:32,351
[Excited]

91
00:04:36,151 --> 00:04:39,941
- Who is it? Who is it?
- Seriously, who is it?

92
00:04:42,141 --> 00:04:44,261
- Huh?
- I think it's Wu Yeol.

93
00:04:45,221 --> 00:04:47,071
It's Seo Won.

94
00:04:49,491 --> 00:04:53,191
- Hello.
- Hello.

95
00:04:53,191 --> 00:04:55,891
- Hello.
- Gosh.

96
00:05:00,271 --> 00:05:03,281
- You read this book.
- Yes.

97
00:05:07,711 --> 00:05:11,671
- It was you, Gyu Ri.
- Hello.

98
00:05:15,981 --> 00:05:18,291
- You read this book.
- Yes.

99
00:05:18,291 --> 00:05:20,251
Did you get to read it a bit?

100
00:05:21,241 --> 00:05:24,171
- It was difficult.
- A little.

101
00:05:24,171 --> 00:05:27,981
But it explains my feelings.

102
00:05:27,981 --> 00:05:30,111
I chose it very carefully.

103
00:05:30,111 --> 00:05:32,581
I didn't think it'd be you.

104
00:05:32,581 --> 00:05:34,701
Thank you so much.

105
00:05:36,261 --> 00:05:38,301
- You're cold, right?
- Yes.

106
00:05:38,301 --> 00:05:40,511
- Shall we go?
- Seo Won is so tall.

107
00:05:40,511 --> 00:05:42,671
Is that book...

108
00:05:42,671 --> 00:05:46,411
really the one you liked?

109
00:05:46,411 --> 00:05:48,111
- Yes.
- When did you read it?

110
00:05:48,111 --> 00:05:50,511
I read it about two or three years ago.

111
00:05:50,511 --> 00:05:53,931
I've been meaning to read it again.

112
00:05:53,931 --> 00:05:57,641
I like his other books, too. Alain de Botton.

113
00:05:59,051 --> 00:06:03,111
Did you read all the books
and choose after deliberating?

114
00:06:03,111 --> 00:06:04,581
Yes.

115
00:06:08,821 --> 00:06:13,181
I liked this book the most.

116
00:06:14,711 --> 00:06:17,441
Was it an indoor shoot today?

117
00:06:17,441 --> 00:06:21,461
- Yes, it was the same thing as yesterday.
- Really?

118
00:06:21,461 --> 00:06:24,941
Did you do a slick-back hairdo?

119
00:06:24,941 --> 00:06:27,861
Some people want that.

120
00:06:27,861 --> 00:06:30,241
I've requested that, too.

121
00:06:30,241 --> 00:06:32,211
Right, you're a director.

122
00:06:32,211 --> 00:06:33,741
Yes, she directs the models.

123
00:06:33,741 --> 00:06:35,931
Slick back isn't my look.

124
00:06:35,931 --> 00:06:39,791
Really? I think you could pull off anything.

125
00:06:40,801 --> 00:06:42,091
Where's your office located?

126
00:06:42,091 --> 00:06:44,391
- Yeonnam-dong.
- Yeonnam-dong.

127
00:06:50,021 --> 00:06:52,301
I've said all this before.

128
00:06:54,021 --> 00:06:57,521
- I can't remember because I was so nervous.
- No, you weren't.

129
00:06:57,521 --> 00:07:00,211
I'm still getting to know everyone.

130
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:02,731
Some get more nervous than others.

131
00:07:02,731 --> 00:07:06,781
You seem to struggle to get to know me.

132
00:07:06,781 --> 00:07:09,681
- Me? You think so?
- Yes.

133
00:07:09,681 --> 00:07:11,221
Why did you think so?

134
00:07:11,221 --> 00:07:14,291
That's just the feeling I get.

135
00:07:17,381 --> 00:07:18,791
Gyu Ri is a good conversationalist.

136
00:07:18,791 --> 00:07:22,031
I think that's her usual personality.

137
00:07:22,031 --> 00:07:26,171
And she's cute and clumsy
in front of Wu Yeol.

138
00:07:26,171 --> 00:07:29,281
It's okay to fall for him, Gyu Ri.

139
00:07:29,281 --> 00:07:33,091
[A restaurant in Seongdong-gu]

140
00:07:35,501 --> 00:07:38,581
Are you very hungry? I am a little.

141
00:07:38,581 --> 00:07:42,671
I'm hungry, too.
I haven't eaten anything all day.

142
00:07:42,671 --> 00:07:45,231
Steak and carbs.

143
00:07:45,231 --> 00:07:48,271
- I want this.
- Risotto? Sounds good.

144
00:07:49,601 --> 00:07:52,261
Should we each have a glass of this?

145
00:07:52,261 --> 00:07:54,401
Sounds good.

146
00:07:54,401 --> 00:07:57,391
I can tell that Seo Won is excited.

147
00:08:00,881 --> 00:08:03,111
[Awkward]

148
00:08:03,111 --> 00:08:04,981
He struggles to make eye contact.

149
00:08:04,981 --> 00:08:08,591
[Awkward silence continues]

150
00:08:09,181 --> 00:08:12,171
How do I talk to him?

151
00:08:13,021 --> 00:08:17,241
It's so hard to read Seo Won.

152
00:08:17,241 --> 00:08:18,951
It went off.

153
00:08:19,811 --> 00:08:22,161
That was fun.

154
00:08:22,161 --> 00:08:25,941
I found him so distant on the first day.

155
00:08:25,941 --> 00:08:29,651
Right. He was like, "Take care."

156
00:08:29,651 --> 00:08:33,811
I just thought,
"He must be unhappy that it's me."

157
00:08:37,451 --> 00:08:39,781
Why is this out?

158
00:08:43,321 --> 00:08:44,921
[Awkward]

159
00:08:46,731 --> 00:08:48,801
Which do you like? White?

160
00:08:48,801 --> 00:08:49,881
[Tap, tap]

161
00:08:50,661 --> 00:08:52,821
- Yellow.
- This?

162
00:08:52,821 --> 00:08:55,241
- This.
- Okay.

163
00:08:56,221 --> 00:08:58,461
- Should I pour you some water?
- Yes.

164
00:08:58,461 --> 00:09:01,341
- Is water okay?
- It'd be great.

165
00:09:01,341 --> 00:09:03,241
Thank you.

166
00:09:10,521 --> 00:09:12,971
You must like knitwear.

167
00:09:12,971 --> 00:09:15,291
- Knitwear.
- Knitwear?

168
00:09:15,291 --> 00:09:18,991
- You're always wearing knitwear.
- You're right.

169
00:09:18,991 --> 00:09:21,641
I like coats and knitwear.

170
00:09:21,641 --> 00:09:24,081
I like clean looks.

171
00:09:24,081 --> 00:09:25,941
You have a nice physique.

172
00:09:25,941 --> 00:09:27,551
Do I?

173
00:09:31,001 --> 00:09:32,701
No...

174
00:09:35,041 --> 00:09:37,251
It's getting kind of exciting.

175
00:09:39,271 --> 00:09:40,431
They're cute.

176
00:09:40,431 --> 00:09:42,061
[The wine came just in time]

177
00:09:42,061 --> 00:09:43,501
Thank you.

178
00:09:43,501 --> 00:09:45,011
[Clank]

179
00:09:54,361 --> 00:09:57,341
Do you want to talk about the book?
Or should we wait?

180
00:09:57,341 --> 00:09:59,961
I do. I've been wanting to.

181
00:10:00,841 --> 00:10:02,041
[Laugh]

182
00:10:04,581 --> 00:10:08,671
You keep drinking alone. It's your habit.

183
00:10:08,671 --> 00:10:11,891
- I'm sorry.
- No, don't be sorry.

184
00:10:12,711 --> 00:10:16,851
This book caught my eye from the first page.

185
00:10:16,851 --> 00:10:20,801
I chose this book because
of its romantic fate theory.

186
00:10:20,801 --> 00:10:23,641
Can I see? Can I see?

187
00:10:23,641 --> 00:10:25,611
You can read it a bit.

188
00:10:32,041 --> 00:10:34,731
[Focused]

189
00:10:34,731 --> 00:10:37,911
[Nervous for some reason]

190
00:10:40,831 --> 00:10:43,241
Do you believe in fate?

191
00:10:43,241 --> 00:10:45,941
- Pardon?
- Do you believe in fate?

192
00:10:45,941 --> 00:10:48,021
I think I have so far.

193
00:10:49,661 --> 00:10:51,611
I think I have.

194
00:10:52,921 --> 00:10:57,961
When it comes to love,

195
00:10:59,301 --> 00:11:04,851
I want to remember it
fondly and romantically.

196
00:11:05,741 --> 00:11:08,541
That's how I want to love.

197
00:11:08,541 --> 00:11:10,781
I love conversations like this.

198
00:11:12,351 --> 00:11:15,181
Is that how you've been dating?

199
00:11:15,181 --> 00:11:17,841
I guess you haven't had bad breakups.

200
00:11:17,841 --> 00:11:19,821
No, it's all been...

201
00:11:24,681 --> 00:11:28,941
- Is it possible to have a good breakup?
- Good breakup?

202
00:11:28,941 --> 00:11:32,391
We've wished each other well, I think.

203
00:11:32,391 --> 00:11:35,371
- Really?
- Yes, I mean it.

204
00:11:37,121 --> 00:11:43,621
I tend to romanticize the past,
even if it wasn't love.

205
00:11:44,621 --> 00:11:47,471
I only remember the good aspects.

206
00:11:49,021 --> 00:11:51,041
- I think so.
- That's nice.

207
00:11:54,251 --> 00:12:01,231
The way you think
is very different from mine.

208
00:12:01,231 --> 00:12:04,661
I'm still not so sure...

209
00:12:05,511 --> 00:12:10,351
if I believe in fate.

210
00:12:11,191 --> 00:12:16,641
So, I tend to doubt stuff like that.

211
00:12:18,191 --> 00:12:20,641
Do you not believe in fate?

212
00:12:21,891 --> 00:12:24,721
My answer is, "I'm not sure yet."

213
00:12:28,131 --> 00:12:32,631
In my mind, fate makes you
fall in love instantly,

214
00:12:32,631 --> 00:12:37,111
things keep working out, and you get married.

215
00:12:37,111 --> 00:12:39,371
That's how I think of it.

216
00:12:40,111 --> 00:12:42,911
Our interpretations are different.

217
00:12:42,911 --> 00:12:45,111
In my mind, fate is...

218
00:12:48,371 --> 00:12:50,121
[Tap]

219
00:12:51,231 --> 00:12:57,591
I chose a book, and we didn't
know each other days ago.

220
00:12:58,911 --> 00:13:02,411
We ended up moving into Signal House.

221
00:13:02,411 --> 00:13:05,241
- Have a seat.
- Hello.

222
00:13:05,241 --> 00:13:07,521
You chose this book.

223
00:13:08,751 --> 00:13:11,211
Oh, my God.

224
00:13:11,211 --> 00:13:14,081
And we're now sitting here together.

225
00:13:14,081 --> 00:13:15,731
I think...

226
00:13:17,421 --> 00:13:21,471
that could be fate. That's what I think.

227
00:13:21,471 --> 00:13:22,351
[Fidgeting]

228
00:13:22,351 --> 00:13:24,171
That's cool.

229
00:13:26,271 --> 00:13:28,981
- This could be fate.
- He's suddenly being sincere.

230
00:13:28,981 --> 00:13:31,491
- It could be fate.
- No way.

231
00:13:33,581 --> 00:13:37,151
Actually, Alain de Botton says that.

232
00:13:37,151 --> 00:13:39,791
That people get confused.

233
00:13:39,791 --> 00:13:44,691
They believe that it's fate whenever
they meet someone new.

234
00:13:44,691 --> 00:13:48,311
They only see the good aspects when you meet

235
00:13:48,311 --> 00:13:52,281
but they start seeing the flaws

236
00:13:52,281 --> 00:13:55,241
and things fall apart.

237
00:13:56,221 --> 00:13:58,671
That's what I think.

238
00:13:59,681 --> 00:14:02,091
But even so,

239
00:14:02,091 --> 00:14:04,531
because of what I've believed in,

240
00:14:04,531 --> 00:14:08,041
I'll continue to believe that it was fate.

241
00:14:08,041 --> 00:14:09,771
He's choosing to believe in fate.

242
00:14:09,771 --> 00:14:13,541
He thinks breakups happen for a reason, too.

243
00:14:20,301 --> 00:14:22,141
I like that.

244
00:14:26,621 --> 00:14:29,351
- He hit the bullseye.
- That was the best line so far.

245
00:14:29,351 --> 00:14:31,691
- He's the real deal.
- Very thoughtful.

246
00:14:31,691 --> 00:14:34,411
He's a serious type.

247
00:14:34,411 --> 00:14:40,851
The look in his eyes changed
while talking about the book.

248
00:14:40,851 --> 00:14:46,171
I've been thinking
about anxiety a lot lately.

249
00:14:46,171 --> 00:14:49,271
I always expect the worst.

250
00:14:49,271 --> 00:14:52,841
- Same here. You think too much, right?
- I do.

251
00:14:52,841 --> 00:14:58,431
I tend to let anxiety consume me.

252
00:14:58,431 --> 00:15:01,281
I tend to feel unsettled.

253
00:15:05,771 --> 00:15:10,041
- But it's never as bad as you think.
- Right, right.

254
00:15:10,041 --> 00:15:13,141
Same with today. It's been so fun.

255
00:15:14,821 --> 00:15:18,201
This isn't something you learn from others.

256
00:15:18,201 --> 00:15:24,771
I'll break away from bias and
negative thoughts through experience.

257
00:15:26,951 --> 00:15:29,941
I got to think of him differently.

258
00:15:29,941 --> 00:15:32,551
- You must've been so hungry.
- I am.

259
00:15:33,461 --> 00:15:35,401
Should we eat before it gets cold?

260
00:15:35,401 --> 00:15:37,111
[Laugh]

261
00:15:37,991 --> 00:15:38,911
Sorry.

262
00:15:38,911 --> 00:15:42,291
I really enjoyed the time.

263
00:15:46,181 --> 00:15:47,971
The steak...

264
00:15:47,971 --> 00:15:50,181
- Look at how he cut the steak.
- Too big?

265
00:15:50,181 --> 00:15:52,321
In big chunks.

266
00:15:52,321 --> 00:15:54,561
He's so attractive.

267
00:15:59,891 --> 00:16:01,371
It's snowing.

268
00:16:01,371 --> 00:16:02,431
Pardon?

269
00:16:02,431 --> 00:16:04,701
I thought it was snowing briefly.

270
00:16:04,701 --> 00:16:06,691
It's really snowing.

271
00:16:06,691 --> 00:16:08,621
I heard it'll snow tonight.

272
00:16:08,621 --> 00:16:10,881
- You know it snowed last night, right?
- I know.

273
00:16:10,881 --> 00:16:16,121
- It's fate.
- Yesterday, I said I wanted to see snow.

274
00:16:16,121 --> 00:16:19,281
- And it actually snowed briefly.
- It came true.

275
00:16:19,281 --> 00:16:23,961
I said I wanted to see the ocean,
and we saw it yesterday.

276
00:16:25,381 --> 00:16:27,571
That's what they call fate.

277
00:16:27,571 --> 00:16:29,831
[Smiling]

278
00:16:31,951 --> 00:16:35,391
[Serendipity, unexpected joy]

279
00:16:35,391 --> 00:16:38,241
- Do you like snow?
- Yes.

280
00:16:40,551 --> 00:16:44,331
- I really love snow.
- It's so pretty right now.

281
00:16:44,331 --> 00:16:46,871
- It's dancing a bit.
- I know.

282
00:16:46,871 --> 00:16:48,511
It's pretty.

283
00:16:48,511 --> 00:16:49,901
[Glancing]

284
00:16:53,621 --> 00:16:57,281
I feel like Seo Won is falling for her, too.

285
00:16:58,931 --> 00:16:59,831
[Clank]

286
00:17:00,431 --> 00:17:02,401
[Staring]

287
00:17:04,091 --> 00:17:06,561
- Can I ask you a question?
- Yes.

288
00:17:06,561 --> 00:17:08,691
I'd love it. It's fun.

289
00:17:09,721 --> 00:17:14,721
I really enjoyed watching Chainsaw Man.

290
00:17:16,221 --> 00:17:21,391
I watched the 2D version with
a friend and the 4D version alone.

291
00:17:21,391 --> 00:17:23,761
I said I did, too. Remember?

292
00:17:23,761 --> 00:17:27,121
I watched the Chainsaw Man movie last year.

293
00:17:27,121 --> 00:17:30,161
I saw it, too. The Movie: Reze Arc.

294
00:17:30,161 --> 00:17:32,081
Are you a fan? I loved it.

295
00:17:32,081 --> 00:17:33,791
I loved it so much.

296
00:17:33,791 --> 00:17:36,451
I watched it in 2D and again in 4D.

297
00:17:36,451 --> 00:17:38,681
I wanted to watch it again, too.

298
00:17:38,681 --> 00:17:42,321
I guess you guys don't watch anime.

299
00:17:43,321 --> 00:17:45,501
I wanted to join in, but I couldn't.

300
00:17:45,501 --> 00:17:46,481
You were like...

301
00:17:46,481 --> 00:17:48,061
[Not interested]

302
00:17:48,061 --> 00:17:49,811
You seemed lost in thought.

303
00:17:49,811 --> 00:17:52,491
I wasn't lost in thought.

304
00:17:52,491 --> 00:17:54,111
Didn't you cry?

305
00:17:54,111 --> 00:17:56,091
I did, of course.

306
00:17:56,091 --> 00:18:01,191
The epilogue scene at the end
revealed so much.

307
00:18:03,691 --> 00:18:06,921
I didn't think I'd cry
watching an anime, either.

308
00:18:06,921 --> 00:18:10,031
- I think that's true love.
- I know.

309
00:18:10,031 --> 00:18:11,801
I'm sorry.

310
00:18:12,801 --> 00:18:14,711
Why are you laughing?

311
00:18:14,711 --> 00:18:18,621
I've never seriously discussed
Chainsaw Man with anyone before.

312
00:18:18,621 --> 00:18:21,141
- Really?
- No one around me watched it.

313
00:18:21,141 --> 00:18:23,151
This is so fun.

314
00:18:23,151 --> 00:18:25,361
I bought flowers for myself, too.

315
00:18:25,361 --> 00:18:27,861
Really? Daisies?

316
00:18:28,791 --> 00:18:30,731
I loved it so much.

317
00:18:32,071 --> 00:18:35,931
I like buying flowers for myself.

318
00:18:35,931 --> 00:18:38,261
I like gifting myself.

319
00:18:40,741 --> 00:18:43,011
Have you done that?

320
00:18:43,011 --> 00:18:45,651
I feel like I'm revealing myself too much.

321
00:18:45,651 --> 00:18:48,441
Why are you so secretive?

322
00:18:49,701 --> 00:18:54,061
I definitely like flowers as gifts.

323
00:18:54,061 --> 00:18:57,701
- You like to receive them?
- I like to give them.

324
00:19:02,601 --> 00:19:04,121
Why?

325
00:19:05,971 --> 00:19:10,961
I imagine how happy the other person will be.

326
00:19:10,961 --> 00:19:14,951
I enjoy buying them,

327
00:19:14,951 --> 00:19:19,381
and seeing how happy
they are receiving them, too.

328
00:19:28,581 --> 00:19:31,271
So romantic!

329
00:19:31,271 --> 00:19:33,541
- Their personalities are compatible.
- Right.

330
00:19:33,541 --> 00:19:36,131
Do you have a type you like?

331
00:19:36,131 --> 00:19:38,241
[Closing eyes]

332
00:19:38,241 --> 00:19:40,321
Type I like?

333
00:19:42,201 --> 00:19:45,411
- There's one thing I can't give up on.
- What is it?

334
00:19:46,431 --> 00:19:49,221
- This is fun.
- But it's a secret.

335
00:19:49,221 --> 00:19:50,431
What is it?

336
00:19:50,431 --> 00:19:52,211
[Shy]

337
00:19:58,151 --> 00:20:00,271
Someone with a pretty smile.

338
00:20:02,591 --> 00:20:08,381
When you're in love,
all you have to do is smile.

339
00:20:10,411 --> 00:20:12,821
I imagine how pretty their smile is.

340
00:20:12,821 --> 00:20:15,531
- Come on.
- "I imagine how pretty their smile is."

341
00:20:15,531 --> 00:20:17,761
My heart fluttered just now.

342
00:20:21,851 --> 00:20:23,571
How about you?

343
00:20:24,501 --> 00:20:28,741
- There's one thing I can't give up, too.
- One thing you can't give up?

344
00:20:28,741 --> 00:20:31,341
You need to tell me. I want to know.

345
00:20:32,321 --> 00:20:35,151
I like someone with a pretty profile.

346
00:20:35,151 --> 00:20:37,141
Pretty profile?

347
00:20:37,141 --> 00:20:39,021
Seo Won has the best profile.

348
00:20:39,021 --> 00:20:42,821
Why? You want to look at them from the side?

349
00:20:42,821 --> 00:20:44,021
[Laugh]

350
00:20:45,351 --> 00:20:47,661
You don't want to see them straight on?

351
00:20:47,661 --> 00:20:50,851
Do you look better
from the left or the right?

352
00:20:50,851 --> 00:20:52,731
The left.

353
00:20:55,271 --> 00:20:58,131
It's the left for me, too.

354
00:20:58,131 --> 00:20:59,481
Really?

355
00:21:00,411 --> 00:21:01,491
[Walking over]

356
00:21:01,491 --> 00:21:03,301
That's so cute.

357
00:21:04,171 --> 00:21:05,971
You look the same.

358
00:21:09,881 --> 00:21:13,921
You're next to someone
more often than you think.

359
00:21:13,921 --> 00:21:18,541
Like when you walk or drive together.

360
00:21:18,541 --> 00:21:22,781
We see each other's profiles often.

361
00:21:23,701 --> 00:21:27,011
[Showing off her profile immediately]

362
00:21:31,271 --> 00:21:34,721
When we first moved in,

363
00:21:34,721 --> 00:21:37,041
I won rock, paper, scissors.

364
00:21:37,041 --> 00:21:39,041
- She's telling him.
- Do you remember?

365
00:21:39,041 --> 00:21:41,311
I picked you, you know.

366
00:21:41,311 --> 00:21:43,691
[The day they moved in]

367
00:21:44,421 --> 00:21:46,981
I choose the one who came last.

368
00:21:46,981 --> 00:21:49,631
- Seo Won?
- The one on the right.

369
00:21:49,631 --> 00:21:51,811
- I won first place.
- Pardon?

370
00:21:51,811 --> 00:21:53,751
- I won first place.
- You did?

371
00:21:53,751 --> 00:21:56,081
Rock, paper, scissors.

372
00:21:56,081 --> 00:21:58,631
I wanted to ask you about that.

373
00:21:59,901 --> 00:22:02,261
To be honest... This is...

374
00:22:02,261 --> 00:22:06,951
- Of course.
- How do I say this?

375
00:22:10,031 --> 00:22:12,241
[Hmm]

376
00:22:13,971 --> 00:22:17,671
- There are two things.
- Two?

377
00:22:17,671 --> 00:22:21,881
Firstly, you had a pretty profile.

378
00:22:21,881 --> 00:22:25,071
Secondly, I thought you were older.

379
00:22:25,071 --> 00:22:27,411
[Flustered]

380
00:22:28,781 --> 00:22:32,971
- That's why I was hesitant just now.
- Really?

381
00:22:32,971 --> 00:22:37,971
I thought you were a very thoughtful elder.

382
00:22:37,971 --> 00:22:40,231
Elder?

383
00:22:40,231 --> 00:22:41,621
I see.

384
00:22:44,041 --> 00:22:46,321
- She's saying he's her ideal type.
- What do we do?

385
00:22:46,321 --> 00:22:49,281
Right. She liked him at first.

386
00:22:52,261 --> 00:22:54,681
I'm sorry, I'm not an elder.

387
00:22:56,601 --> 00:22:59,261
But unexpectedly...

388
00:22:59,261 --> 00:23:03,531
- I shouldn't have said, "unexpectedly."
- No, be honest.

389
00:23:03,531 --> 00:23:05,491
I don't mind.

390
00:23:05,491 --> 00:23:07,871
Unexpectedly,

391
00:23:10,601 --> 00:23:13,031
you're mature.

392
00:23:15,281 --> 00:23:17,361
- This is not good.
- It's okay. It's okay.

393
00:23:17,361 --> 00:23:20,331
That's how you felt. I understand.

394
00:23:20,331 --> 00:23:22,711
She's so cute when she's acting naturally.

395
00:23:22,711 --> 00:23:25,511
He's someone she can be honest with.

396
00:23:25,511 --> 00:23:28,621
Thanks for saying
I'm more mature than expected.

397
00:23:30,741 --> 00:23:34,421
People in the house don't know you yet.

398
00:23:34,421 --> 00:23:37,721
Everyone moves at a different pace.

399
00:23:37,721 --> 00:23:40,431
Do you observe people for a long time?

400
00:23:40,431 --> 00:23:41,791
Yes.

401
00:23:42,591 --> 00:23:48,091
I talk a lot and spend a lot of time together

402
00:23:50,761 --> 00:23:53,841
before I make up my mind.

403
00:23:55,041 --> 00:24:01,251
Once I make up my mind, I try not to change.

404
00:24:02,581 --> 00:24:04,781
That's how I am.

405
00:24:11,791 --> 00:24:15,081
We were right about him being undecided.

406
00:24:15,081 --> 00:24:17,321
- I thought he was impatient on Day 1.
- I know.

407
00:24:17,321 --> 00:24:19,761
He wasn't being unfriendly
during the 1:1 chat.

408
00:24:19,761 --> 00:24:21,541
He wasn't.

409
00:24:21,541 --> 00:24:23,301
He's just slow-paced.

410
00:24:23,301 --> 00:24:26,121
The view behind you is so pretty.

411
00:24:27,781 --> 00:24:30,661
Gosh, that's the profile she likes.

412
00:24:30,661 --> 00:24:33,131
I'm looking at you and the snow.

413
00:24:33,131 --> 00:24:35,091
It's a snowy view.

414
00:24:36,501 --> 00:24:39,591
I love it when someone has...

415
00:24:40,681 --> 00:24:41,961
a nice profile.

416
00:24:41,961 --> 00:24:43,151
[Smiling]

417
00:24:43,151 --> 00:24:45,171
You're so happy.

418
00:24:47,151 --> 00:24:49,271
Of course, I am.

419
00:24:51,151 --> 00:24:53,081
So funny.

420
00:24:54,401 --> 00:24:55,741
So funny.

421
00:24:55,741 --> 00:24:57,661
I'm happy, of course.

422
00:25:04,381 --> 00:25:06,901
[They're getting to know each other better]

423
00:25:06,901 --> 00:25:09,111
- This is fun.
- Yes.

424
00:25:10,741 --> 00:25:12,761
- My heart is fluttering.
- What's their deal?

425
00:25:12,761 --> 00:25:14,811
- I support this couple.
- Me, too.

426
00:25:14,811 --> 00:25:17,391
- I loved their conversation.
- I know. That was...

427
00:25:17,391 --> 00:25:19,851
- So heart-fluttering.
- I know.

428
00:25:22,381 --> 00:25:26,651
[Heading to the next spot,
walking in the snow]

429
00:25:28,511 --> 00:25:31,501
What? This is my kind of place.

430
00:25:31,501 --> 00:25:33,631
A snack bar on a snowy night? That's amazing.

431
00:25:33,631 --> 00:25:35,481
What should we get?

432
00:25:35,481 --> 00:25:38,051
- Something brothy since it's cold?
- Yes.

433
00:25:38,051 --> 00:25:39,441
Fishcake soup.

434
00:25:39,441 --> 00:25:42,451
- I was looking at that, too.
- Sounds good, right?

435
00:25:43,431 --> 00:25:44,891
1:1? 1:2?

436
00:25:44,891 --> 00:25:47,091
I think 1:1.

437
00:25:49,121 --> 00:25:52,551
- Just going with the feel?
- Yes.

438
00:25:52,551 --> 00:25:54,211
Cheers.

439
00:25:54,211 --> 00:25:55,691
[Gulp]

440
00:25:55,691 --> 00:25:57,561
His profile. His profile.

441
00:25:57,561 --> 00:25:58,891
[Glancing]

442
00:25:58,891 --> 00:26:01,451
You know how to drink.
You chug the first glass.

443
00:26:01,451 --> 00:26:03,091
It's good.

444
00:26:04,371 --> 00:26:07,001
I think I'm teaching you bad things.

445
00:26:07,001 --> 00:26:08,991
- Thank you.
- Enjoy.

446
00:26:08,991 --> 00:26:10,661
[Boiling]

447
00:26:10,661 --> 00:26:13,431
Before we eat...

448
00:26:13,431 --> 00:26:16,141
- This is our first date.
- Yes.

449
00:26:16,141 --> 00:26:18,351
- Should we take a selfie?
- Sounds good.

450
00:26:18,351 --> 00:26:20,501
I'll take it horizontally.

451
00:26:22,281 --> 00:26:23,821
[Click, click]

452
00:26:24,511 --> 00:26:27,201
[Click, click]

453
00:26:27,201 --> 00:26:29,281
[Shutter sound capturing the memories]

454
00:26:29,281 --> 00:26:31,321
Did I take too many?

455
00:26:31,321 --> 00:26:33,601
They look great!

456
00:26:38,061 --> 00:26:40,491
I'll remember that you can't handle spice.

457
00:26:40,491 --> 00:26:41,971
Okay.

458
00:26:43,011 --> 00:26:44,531
Thank you.

459
00:26:46,141 --> 00:26:48,841
That comment. He's so sensitive.

460
00:26:48,841 --> 00:26:51,541
Seriously. "I'll remember."

461
00:26:51,541 --> 00:26:55,531
He has so many different sides.

462
00:27:00,461 --> 00:27:04,911
I'm very happy with what we ordered.

463
00:27:04,911 --> 00:27:07,031
Really? I'm glad.

464
00:27:14,441 --> 00:27:18,641
I don't drink very often, but I like chatting

465
00:27:18,641 --> 00:27:23,731
candidly with people over drinks.

466
00:27:23,731 --> 00:27:26,011
- But I've never done it before.
- What?

467
00:27:26,011 --> 00:27:28,961
All of my...

468
00:27:28,961 --> 00:27:31,661
- exes didn't drink much.
- Really?

469
00:27:31,661 --> 00:27:34,571
I've always wanted to try.
I've fantasized about it.

470
00:27:34,571 --> 00:27:36,071
His exes?

471
00:27:36,071 --> 00:27:40,341
I have an ideal type I forgot to mention.

472
00:27:40,341 --> 00:27:43,701
- I like someone who drinks, too.
- Really?

473
00:27:43,701 --> 00:27:45,991
- I like pairing drinks with food.
- Me, too.

474
00:27:45,991 --> 00:27:48,641
We need to be able to enjoy that together.

475
00:27:48,641 --> 00:27:51,181
If they can't...

476
00:27:51,181 --> 00:27:55,061
I have to drink alone while the
other person is drinking Coke.

477
00:27:55,061 --> 00:27:57,451
- I know.
- Right?

478
00:27:58,521 --> 00:28:00,821
I can't agree more.

479
00:28:00,821 --> 00:28:05,201
They're perfect together. It's meant to be.

480
00:28:05,201 --> 00:28:08,751
Have you always been with people your age?

481
00:28:08,751 --> 00:28:10,781
In relationships?

482
00:28:12,181 --> 00:28:14,421
To be honest,

483
00:28:15,351 --> 00:28:17,531
I've only dated older women.

484
00:28:17,531 --> 00:28:20,831
- What?
- I've only dated older women.

485
00:28:20,831 --> 00:28:23,461
I'm so shocked.

486
00:28:23,461 --> 00:28:25,691
Didn't you expect that?

487
00:28:30,361 --> 00:28:33,421
Don't you want to try dating
someone younger, then?

488
00:28:33,421 --> 00:28:36,661
- I don't think I'm interested.
- Why?

489
00:28:36,661 --> 00:28:43,331
Since I started working
professionally when I was 20...

490
00:28:43,331 --> 00:28:45,201
And I...

491
00:28:47,871 --> 00:28:49,491
To be honest,

492
00:28:51,011 --> 00:28:53,501
I tend to forge ahead.

493
00:28:53,501 --> 00:28:57,881
I express my feelings honestly to someone.

494
00:28:57,881 --> 00:29:02,701
I've been with older women
who understood that.

495
00:29:05,271 --> 00:29:07,081
Is that unexpected?

496
00:29:08,141 --> 00:29:11,691
Yes. That surprises me the most.

497
00:29:11,691 --> 00:29:15,971
- He dates older women, not like Wu Yeol.
- They're different.

498
00:29:15,971 --> 00:29:18,131
Have you dated younger men?

499
00:29:18,131 --> 00:29:19,781
I've only dated older men.

500
00:29:19,781 --> 00:29:22,611
Really? Really?

501
00:29:23,501 --> 00:29:25,581
That's so unexpected.

502
00:29:28,071 --> 00:29:29,481
I'm honored.

503
00:29:29,481 --> 00:29:31,641
I am, too.

504
00:29:31,641 --> 00:29:34,481
But it's not that different, is it?

505
00:29:35,841 --> 00:29:40,071
Well, no. It really isn't, to be honest.

506
00:29:45,421 --> 00:29:49,131
I think we're getting to know each other.

507
00:29:49,131 --> 00:29:52,261
I didn't know until I came here, either.

508
00:29:52,261 --> 00:29:55,331
I realized how cautious I could be.

509
00:29:55,331 --> 00:30:00,231
I got to reconfirm how I am.

510
00:30:00,231 --> 00:30:02,681
I'm learning about myself, too.

511
00:30:06,631 --> 00:30:09,181
How do you feel, facing yourself?

512
00:30:09,181 --> 00:30:14,541
I think I'm accepting everything.
I don't want to deny it.

513
00:30:17,371 --> 00:30:22,021
I had a similar thought, too.

514
00:30:24,301 --> 00:30:28,451
- I had a tough time yesterday.
- Really?

515
00:30:31,171 --> 00:30:35,201
You're so wise. You're helpful.

516
00:30:35,201 --> 00:30:37,981
I liked what you said just now.

517
00:30:43,591 --> 00:30:46,861
She's opening herself up a lot.

518
00:30:46,861 --> 00:30:53,571
[They're facing their new sides today]

519
00:30:53,571 --> 00:30:56,731
- Wow.
- We melted.

520
00:30:56,731 --> 00:30:58,771
[The studio has melted]

521
00:30:58,771 --> 00:31:00,581
We totally got sucked in.

522
00:31:00,581 --> 00:31:04,041
Can we not say anything
and enjoy this briefly?

523
00:31:04,041 --> 00:31:06,861
Return your pay, then.

524
00:31:06,861 --> 00:31:10,821
It was like watching
the "Before Sunrise" series.

525
00:31:10,821 --> 00:31:14,391
Everything they said wasn't said lightly.

526
00:31:14,391 --> 00:31:19,381
She seemed a lot more comfortable
and natural than with Wu Yeol.

527
00:31:19,381 --> 00:31:24,131
I liked how she was more true to herself.

528
00:31:24,131 --> 00:31:26,061
She gets to be herself.

529
00:31:26,061 --> 00:31:29,601
Can she be more herself with Seo Won?

530
00:31:29,601 --> 00:31:31,111
It's getting tricky.

531
00:31:31,111 --> 00:31:34,401
Seo Won was a surprise to the viewers and us.

532
00:31:34,401 --> 00:31:37,281
We thought he was a cute and immature type,

533
00:31:37,281 --> 00:31:41,091
but he was that thoughtful of a person?

534
00:31:41,091 --> 00:31:45,651
I could tell Gyu Ri was being moved by that.

535
00:31:45,651 --> 00:31:49,551
I realized how biased I was, too.

536
00:31:49,551 --> 00:31:52,391
I feel bad for thinking he couldn't be deep

537
00:31:52,391 --> 00:31:54,001
since he's tall and handsome.

538
00:31:54,001 --> 00:31:56,211
- You were biased.
- I was.

539
00:31:56,211 --> 00:31:57,481
I'm so sorry.

540
00:31:57,481 --> 00:32:04,141
The moment she thought, "Is he cool?" was

541
00:32:04,141 --> 00:32:06,721
when they talked about fate.

542
00:32:06,721 --> 00:32:08,621
- Although they disagreed.
- Yes, even so.

543
00:32:08,621 --> 00:32:11,441
She asked casually, but he answered...

544
00:32:11,441 --> 00:32:13,301
You chose this book.

545
00:32:13,301 --> 00:32:16,041
And we're now sitting here together.

546
00:32:16,041 --> 00:32:19,941
I think that could be fate.

547
00:32:19,941 --> 00:32:21,921
His answer was so cool.

548
00:32:21,921 --> 00:32:23,891
That was the best scene if this were a drama.

549
00:32:23,891 --> 00:32:29,111
Whether Gyu Ri will change her mind
about seeing younger men

550
00:32:29,111 --> 00:32:33,141
will decide the fate of this relationship.

551
00:32:33,141 --> 00:32:36,971
She thought someone who could
provide comfort to her

552
00:32:36,971 --> 00:32:40,701
in everyday life was someone older.

553
00:32:40,701 --> 00:32:45,081
Once you decide that,
you don't consider younger men.

554
00:32:45,081 --> 00:32:46,481
But it's not true.

555
00:32:46,481 --> 00:32:51,161
She could've easily considered
dating a younger man today.

556
00:32:51,161 --> 00:32:55,351
In the end, I think Gyu Ri will fall for him.

557
00:32:55,351 --> 00:32:57,681
- Really?
- I thought so, too.

558
00:32:57,681 --> 00:33:03,601
I feel like she's been heartbroken
in the past.

559
00:33:03,601 --> 00:33:07,701
She likes Wu Yeol. She likes him a lot,

560
00:33:07,701 --> 00:33:11,941
but she's afraid to get hurt.
I think she'll get anxious.

561
00:33:11,941 --> 00:33:16,671
I feel like Seo Won might help her
when she struggles.

562
00:33:16,671 --> 00:33:18,561
- Right.
- He really showcased himself.

563
00:33:18,561 --> 00:33:20,681
I think Seo Won will be fun to watch.

564
00:33:20,681 --> 00:33:23,491
Totally. We're just getting started.

565
00:33:23,491 --> 00:33:25,761
We might all fall for him.

566
00:33:26,831 --> 00:33:31,551
[Under the warm winter sun]

567
00:33:31,551 --> 00:33:36,211
[Yu Gyeong is waiting for her date]

568
00:33:39,361 --> 00:33:40,521
[Last night]

569
00:33:41,731 --> 00:33:43,861
I think I know who this is.

570
00:33:43,861 --> 00:33:45,631
[Bothered]

571
00:33:45,631 --> 00:33:48,011
- I think I know.
- This one?

572
00:33:48,011 --> 00:33:51,141
This is Wu Yeol's, I think.

573
00:33:52,101 --> 00:33:54,221
That's your hunch?

574
00:33:54,221 --> 00:33:58,341
Is there a book you want if you knew
which one belonged to whom?

575
00:33:58,341 --> 00:34:02,611
I want to talk to the person
who read this book.

576
00:34:06,361 --> 00:34:08,771
I... I think I have one.

577
00:34:09,681 --> 00:34:12,271
[The question made her think of someone]

578
00:34:14,031 --> 00:34:18,231
If Wu Yeol is leaning that direction...

579
00:34:20,571 --> 00:34:23,401
I'll choose this, then.

580
00:34:23,401 --> 00:34:25,581
Yu Gyeong let her have it.

581
00:34:26,561 --> 00:34:31,871
I didn't think I could erase the feelings.

582
00:34:34,961 --> 00:34:39,621
I have no idea who will come.

583
00:34:40,621 --> 00:34:44,431
So, I kept feeling nervous.

584
00:34:44,431 --> 00:34:47,511
[Whose book did Yu Gyeong choose?]

585
00:34:51,001 --> 00:34:52,901
Isn't that Wu Yeol?

586
00:35:01,331 --> 00:35:05,911
[Someone she can't help but look at,
even if she tried to look away]

587
00:35:10,231 --> 00:35:11,301
It's Wu Yeol!

588
00:35:11,301 --> 00:35:13,691
- It's Wu Yeol!
- No way.

589
00:35:13,691 --> 00:35:15,431
So crazy!

590
00:35:17,881 --> 00:35:19,801
Look at her smile. Look at her smile.

591
00:35:19,801 --> 00:35:22,241
And Wu Yeol came.

592
00:35:25,411 --> 00:35:27,961
Look at her face. My gosh.

593
00:35:29,351 --> 00:35:35,081
[Yu Gyeong's date is Wu Yeol]

594
00:35:40,841 --> 00:35:42,851
Really?

595
00:35:46,961 --> 00:35:49,211
[Shocked]

596
00:35:53,891 --> 00:35:55,581
What...

597
00:35:56,751 --> 00:35:58,391
What's this?

598
00:36:00,051 --> 00:36:01,451
Why?

599
00:36:03,001 --> 00:36:05,141
- What's the deal?
- Why?

600
00:36:05,141 --> 00:36:06,821
It's nothing.

601
00:36:06,821 --> 00:36:09,421
- Shall we go?
- Let's go.

602
00:36:12,841 --> 00:36:14,461
Oh, my God.

603
00:36:14,461 --> 00:36:17,551
- Wow.
- This is fate.

604
00:36:17,551 --> 00:36:21,541
She looks so happy, but...

605
00:36:23,011 --> 00:36:25,901
"My savior who came to ruin me."

606
00:36:28,471 --> 00:36:30,151
I really had no clue.

607
00:36:30,151 --> 00:36:32,501
- Really?
- Yes.

608
00:36:33,421 --> 00:36:35,461
I think...

609
00:36:38,751 --> 00:36:41,731
- I was hoping for this.
- Really?

610
00:36:42,771 --> 00:36:44,611
You're lying.

611
00:36:46,951 --> 00:36:48,011
[Scream]

612
00:36:48,011 --> 00:36:49,611
"I think I was hoping for this"?

613
00:36:49,611 --> 00:36:51,061
- Hold on.
- Hey, hey.

614
00:36:51,061 --> 00:36:53,831
- Hey, hey.
- He can't say that.

615
00:36:53,831 --> 00:36:55,781
No one's committed yet, guys.

616
00:36:55,781 --> 00:36:58,001
I know. I know, but...

617
00:36:58,001 --> 00:37:00,241
You aren't disappointed
that it's me, are you?

618
00:37:00,241 --> 00:37:02,821
No, not at all.

619
00:37:02,821 --> 00:37:06,291
But I thought it might happen.

620
00:37:06,291 --> 00:37:08,711
When you chose this neighborhood...

621
00:37:08,711 --> 00:37:11,301
I have my usual spots.

622
00:37:11,301 --> 00:37:15,481
- Your favorite spots?
- Yes, I wanted to go to those spots.

623
00:37:15,481 --> 00:37:16,891
That's cool.

624
00:37:16,891 --> 00:37:19,341
Who did you think it was?

625
00:37:19,341 --> 00:37:20,921
She can't hide her feelings.

626
00:37:20,921 --> 00:37:22,901
- I don't know.
- Should I not ask?

627
00:37:22,901 --> 00:37:25,501
No, I don't know.

628
00:37:26,781 --> 00:37:29,091
Whatever.

629
00:37:29,091 --> 00:37:30,941
This is crazy.

630
00:37:32,001 --> 00:37:34,131
- You haven't eaten, right?
- No, I haven't.

631
00:37:34,131 --> 00:37:35,561
- Are you hungry?
- I am.

632
00:37:35,561 --> 00:37:39,621
I was so, so, so nervous, to be honest.

633
00:37:39,621 --> 00:37:42,451
- Since this morning?
- Yes.

634
00:37:42,451 --> 00:37:46,451
You couldn't eat yesterday.
You have to eat today.

635
00:37:46,451 --> 00:37:49,161
I have to. I should relax now.

636
00:37:49,161 --> 00:37:51,741
- I feel totally relaxed now.
- Really?

637
00:37:51,741 --> 00:37:55,151
Her ailment was gone the moment she saw him.

638
00:38:00,821 --> 00:38:03,161
They look good together.

639
00:38:09,381 --> 00:38:11,531
I'm not sure if you'd like it.

640
00:38:12,501 --> 00:38:16,121
- It's this way.
- This way?

641
00:38:16,121 --> 00:38:20,031
- Have you been here?
- Of course. I'm a regular.

642
00:38:21,271 --> 00:38:23,911
[Wu Yeol's favorite cafe]

643
00:38:26,321 --> 00:38:28,441
Look at her expression.

644
00:38:28,441 --> 00:38:30,071
Should we order?

645
00:38:30,071 --> 00:38:32,621
- Yes.
- What would you like?

646
00:38:39,361 --> 00:38:41,731
I want the matcha latte.

647
00:38:41,731 --> 00:38:43,731
I should look at this.

648
00:38:44,911 --> 00:38:46,461
[Wu Yeol's book]

649
00:38:46,461 --> 00:38:48,411
Did you finish it?

650
00:38:49,431 --> 00:38:51,141
Actually...

651
00:38:52,371 --> 00:38:56,551
I didn't want to choose this book at first.

652
00:38:57,551 --> 00:39:02,121
- Why not?
- I didn't think I should because...

653
00:39:04,781 --> 00:39:07,611
It says, "animalistic attraction."

654
00:39:07,611 --> 00:39:11,811
- It's all about basic instincts.
- Scientific stuff.

655
00:39:11,811 --> 00:39:15,611
- Yes, scientific and...
- It's like a theory on love.

656
00:39:15,611 --> 00:39:17,431
Dopamine, too.

657
00:39:18,561 --> 00:39:20,231
Are you hooked now?

658
00:39:20,231 --> 00:39:22,381
Is this for real?

659
00:39:22,381 --> 00:39:25,811
- I'm curious.
- I don't know.

660
00:39:27,891 --> 00:39:30,241
To be honest...

661
00:39:30,241 --> 00:39:34,371
when you think about why
you're attracted to someone,

662
00:39:34,371 --> 00:39:37,941
you tend to be attracted
to someone different.

663
00:39:37,941 --> 00:39:41,311
Someone you've never
experienced before, you know.

664
00:39:41,311 --> 00:39:44,011
- Right. I saw that.
- So...

665
00:39:44,011 --> 00:39:49,571
since I'm like that, I thought
others were like that, too.

666
00:39:54,901 --> 00:39:57,781
Someone with the opposite tendencies?

667
00:39:57,781 --> 00:40:01,521
I know what my personality is like.

668
00:40:01,521 --> 00:40:05,281
But when I came here,

669
00:40:05,281 --> 00:40:09,011
there were people
I hadn't experienced before.

670
00:40:10,091 --> 00:40:13,041
And among them...

671
00:40:15,701 --> 00:40:18,051
I was curious a bit.

672
00:40:19,801 --> 00:40:25,921
I thought you behaved differently from me.

673
00:40:25,921 --> 00:40:27,651
- Me?
- Yes.

674
00:40:27,651 --> 00:40:29,791
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

675
00:40:31,271 --> 00:40:33,651
You seem introverted.

676
00:40:33,651 --> 00:40:37,221
You talk less in a group, too.

677
00:40:37,221 --> 00:40:39,571
[First night]

678
00:40:39,571 --> 00:40:44,591
[It was their first time together,
but they weren't awkward]

679
00:40:50,831 --> 00:40:52,201
[Concerned]

680
00:40:52,201 --> 00:40:54,471
He's been observing her.

681
00:40:55,751 --> 00:40:58,811
But on the other hand, I'm okay in a group.

682
00:40:58,811 --> 00:41:01,261
Really?

683
00:41:01,261 --> 00:41:06,181
That's why you were one of the
people I was curious about.

684
00:41:06,181 --> 00:41:08,211
He has a bit of feelings for her.

685
00:41:08,211 --> 00:41:10,501
You thought I was different.

686
00:41:10,501 --> 00:41:13,081
I can usually see
if someone's adjusting okay.

687
00:41:13,081 --> 00:41:15,261
I thought I was good at detecting it.

688
00:41:15,261 --> 00:41:18,641
But you're more unpredictable than I thought.

689
00:41:18,641 --> 00:41:24,271
I failed to read you.
So, I'm kind of curious.

690
00:41:24,271 --> 00:41:27,941
- I'm curious what you think.
- He's digging deep.

691
00:41:30,861 --> 00:41:33,711
I'm not good at revealing my true feelings.

692
00:41:33,711 --> 00:41:36,831
Right? You seem to hide them.

693
00:41:36,831 --> 00:41:38,001
[Busted]

694
00:41:38,001 --> 00:41:39,841
It's obvious.

695
00:41:42,511 --> 00:41:44,411
Your expression was like,

696
00:41:44,411 --> 00:41:48,211
"Why do you read stuff like this?" at first.

697
00:41:48,211 --> 00:41:51,621
- That was just the impression I got.
- Okay.

698
00:41:51,621 --> 00:41:55,521
- Let's read it together later...
- Together? Like this?

699
00:41:58,841 --> 00:42:00,371
What do you think?

700
00:42:00,371 --> 00:42:02,631
- I like the vibe.
- Right?

701
00:42:02,631 --> 00:42:06,571
I come here almost every day after work.

702
00:42:06,571 --> 00:42:08,521
Really?

703
00:42:13,091 --> 00:42:14,541
[Hesitant]

704
00:42:16,691 --> 00:42:21,461
I have many questions,
but they're too direct.

705
00:42:21,461 --> 00:42:26,291
Did I ask who you wanted to see?

706
00:42:26,291 --> 00:42:28,491
What? Are you sounding me out?

707
00:42:28,491 --> 00:42:30,251
I'm curious.

708
00:42:42,761 --> 00:42:43,781
[Working up courage]

709
00:42:43,781 --> 00:42:46,341
- I wanted to talk to you.
- Really?

710
00:42:46,341 --> 00:42:47,631
Of course.

711
00:42:47,631 --> 00:42:50,731
My gosh. She's showing her feelings.

712
00:42:50,731 --> 00:42:51,901
[Nodding]

713
00:42:52,551 --> 00:42:54,371
[Hesitant]

714
00:42:54,371 --> 00:42:57,141
- She's blushing.
- My gosh!

715
00:42:58,491 --> 00:43:00,611
Are you nervous?

716
00:43:00,611 --> 00:43:02,521
Is it because you're cold?

717
00:43:02,521 --> 00:43:04,661
- That was crazy just now.
- Wu Yeol is attractive.

718
00:43:04,661 --> 00:43:06,101
- He is.
- "Are you nervous?"

719
00:43:06,101 --> 00:43:08,221
Wow, crazy.

720
00:43:16,371 --> 00:43:20,571
It could be that I'm cold, this,

721
00:43:20,571 --> 00:43:22,951
or the situation.

722
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,991
It's one of those three.

723
00:43:27,151 --> 00:43:28,811
I don't know.

724
00:43:38,691 --> 00:43:44,401
[She's speechless after blurting
out her true feelings]

725
00:43:45,651 --> 00:43:47,151
[Smiling]

726
00:43:48,721 --> 00:43:51,131
[Awkward]

727
00:43:58,531 --> 00:44:00,711
[Fidgeting]

728
00:44:02,921 --> 00:44:09,541
I talked to you casually, without asking,
after finding out your age.

729
00:44:09,541 --> 00:44:11,131
- You did?
- Yes.

730
00:44:11,131 --> 00:44:14,941
I thought, "She's younger.
I should talk to her casually."

731
00:44:14,941 --> 00:44:16,211
I think it came out naturally.

732
00:44:16,211 --> 00:44:19,281
- I'm the only one younger than you.
- Right.

733
00:44:19,281 --> 00:44:20,881
He's doing it again.

734
00:44:20,881 --> 00:44:22,261
Yes, ma'am.

735
00:44:22,261 --> 00:44:23,961
That was awkward.

736
00:44:23,961 --> 00:44:25,561
They're both cute.

737
00:44:25,561 --> 00:44:28,301
Really? Do you prefer to talk casually?

738
00:44:28,301 --> 00:44:31,211
It doesn't matter to me. What do you think?

739
00:44:31,211 --> 00:44:36,091
I prefer talking formally to someone older.

740
00:44:36,961 --> 00:44:40,671
- Talk formally, then.
- But, but...

741
00:44:40,671 --> 00:44:43,971
I prefer someone to talk to me casually.

742
00:44:46,111 --> 00:44:47,591
Casually?

743
00:44:48,591 --> 00:44:53,241
Right before we met, I saw someone standing.

744
00:44:53,241 --> 00:44:55,881
She had a familiar silhouette.

745
00:44:55,881 --> 00:44:59,891
I saw it and thought, "It's Yu Gyeong."

746
00:45:01,481 --> 00:45:02,811
[Shy]

747
00:45:02,811 --> 00:45:05,791
Gosh, she's loving it right now.

748
00:45:05,791 --> 00:45:08,541
I have a talent.

749
00:45:08,541 --> 00:45:10,321
I'm good at recognizing people.

750
00:45:10,321 --> 00:45:13,031
From where could you tell?

751
00:45:13,031 --> 00:45:14,481
- From far away?
- Yes, far away.

752
00:45:14,481 --> 00:45:17,881
- You could tell right away?
- Of course.

753
00:45:17,881 --> 00:45:19,801
So...

754
00:45:19,801 --> 00:45:21,781
Yes.

755
00:45:21,781 --> 00:45:24,821
- Did I pass?
- Pass?

756
00:45:24,821 --> 00:45:27,241
- Never seen her laugh like that.
- Yes, you pass.

757
00:45:27,241 --> 00:45:30,671
She's so charming today.

758
00:45:30,671 --> 00:45:35,651
I thought, "If it's Yu Gyeong,

759
00:45:35,651 --> 00:45:38,361
how will I satisfy her childish taste buds?"

760
00:45:38,361 --> 00:45:40,781
You don't drink...

761
00:45:40,781 --> 00:45:45,651
I eat everything. I just don't eat seafood.

762
00:45:45,651 --> 00:45:47,321
- I thought of something I like.
- What?

763
00:45:47,321 --> 00:45:49,801
- Hamburgers.
- From where?

764
00:45:49,801 --> 00:45:52,381
Mozzarella in the Burger.

765
00:45:52,381 --> 00:45:54,621
- It's really tasty.
- I've tried it.

766
00:45:54,621 --> 00:45:56,301
It has bacon in it, too.

767
00:45:56,301 --> 00:45:57,751
[Cute]

768
00:45:57,751 --> 00:46:00,451
- He thinks she's cute.
- You're a kid.

769
00:46:00,451 --> 00:46:03,561
You like the stretchy mozzarella, right?

770
00:46:06,551 --> 00:46:11,231
- Of course. I like doing this.
- You like cheese sticks, too?

771
00:46:14,801 --> 00:46:17,521
I'll put this on my lips quickly.

772
00:46:18,831 --> 00:46:20,701
Me, too.

773
00:46:22,201 --> 00:46:28,161
[Time to put on lip balm]

774
00:46:28,161 --> 00:46:29,961
[Glancing]

775
00:46:31,021 --> 00:46:33,471
Are your lips naturally that red?

776
00:46:33,471 --> 00:46:34,931
Yes.

777
00:46:34,931 --> 00:46:37,911
Daebak. What's your secret?

778
00:46:40,611 --> 00:46:42,181
I bite them.

779
00:46:44,431 --> 00:46:46,751
[They're red because he bites them]

780
00:46:48,941 --> 00:46:50,671
[Staring]

781
00:46:50,671 --> 00:46:53,241
- Wow.
- She can't stop staring.

782
00:46:55,241 --> 00:46:58,891
- Bite them.
- Yu Gyeong is smitten.

783
00:46:58,891 --> 00:47:02,621
[She can't stop looking at him]

784
00:47:03,131 --> 00:47:06,751
Should we have bungeoppang today?

785
00:47:06,751 --> 00:47:08,151
Bungeoppang?

786
00:47:08,151 --> 00:47:10,391
- Do you like bungeoppang?
- Of course.

787
00:47:10,391 --> 00:47:13,311
- Do you like pastries?
- Yes, I do.

788
00:47:14,661 --> 00:47:17,501
- What kind of pastries do you like?
- I eat all kinds.

789
00:47:17,501 --> 00:47:20,021
- All kinds?
- I like financiers, too.

790
00:47:20,021 --> 00:47:22,261
He wanted to say salt bread,
but didn't want to be found out.

791
00:47:22,261 --> 00:47:23,701
[Suspicious]

792
00:47:29,021 --> 00:47:31,381
I want to drink.

793
00:47:33,101 --> 00:47:35,471
- Draft beer?
- No.

794
00:47:35,471 --> 00:47:37,921
- Soju.
- Soju?

795
00:47:39,531 --> 00:47:41,031
Soju...

796
00:47:42,031 --> 00:47:43,341
["I want to drink"]

797
00:47:43,341 --> 00:47:44,601
That line.

798
00:47:44,601 --> 00:47:45,891
She drank soda yesterday.

799
00:47:45,891 --> 00:47:48,061
"I want to drink." That was too direct.

800
00:47:48,061 --> 00:47:50,781
Right. It's game over already.

801
00:47:50,781 --> 00:47:55,191
- I guess he does that to women.
- He does that to all women.

802
00:47:55,191 --> 00:47:59,231
For dinner, do you like pasta?

803
00:47:59,231 --> 00:48:00,881
Of course.

804
00:48:01,621 --> 00:48:03,161
There's a car.

805
00:48:10,571 --> 00:48:13,171
- Come inside.
- So attentive.

806
00:48:16,301 --> 00:48:17,751
I hope you like it.

807
00:48:17,751 --> 00:48:19,511
We'll see.

808
00:48:20,311 --> 00:48:23,401
- We'll see?
- We shall see.

809
00:48:23,401 --> 00:48:25,231
[Saw something]

810
00:48:25,771 --> 00:48:28,911
[Found a Dubai chocolate cookie place
on the way]

811
00:48:28,911 --> 00:48:32,021
- Do they sell them?
- Should we get some?

812
00:48:32,021 --> 00:48:33,971
"Should we get some?" Isn't that nice?

813
00:48:33,971 --> 00:48:35,471
Dubai chocolate cookies?

814
00:48:35,471 --> 00:48:37,861
- Should we get them?
- Really?

815
00:48:38,621 --> 00:48:40,571
[Happy]

816
00:48:40,571 --> 00:48:42,461
My gosh.

817
00:48:43,311 --> 00:48:45,971
- Hello.
- Hello.

818
00:48:45,971 --> 00:48:48,191
- Is there an order limit?
- There isn't.

819
00:48:48,191 --> 00:48:52,311
- How many? For everyone?
- One per person?

820
00:48:52,311 --> 00:48:55,091
Two each?

821
00:48:55,091 --> 00:48:58,191
That will be 200,000 won.

822
00:48:58,191 --> 00:49:00,531
- It's on me.
- It's on Oppa.

823
00:49:00,531 --> 00:49:02,421
Seriously? Daebak.

824
00:49:02,421 --> 00:49:05,901
- I'm impressed.
- Dubai chocolate cookies.

825
00:49:05,901 --> 00:49:06,901
[Freshly made Dubai chocolate cookies]

826
00:49:06,901 --> 00:49:09,991
- They're tasty, right?
- They're freshly made.

827
00:49:09,991 --> 00:49:11,931
Gosh, daebak.

828
00:49:12,761 --> 00:49:14,421
I'm happy.

829
00:49:15,241 --> 00:49:17,661
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

830
00:49:17,661 --> 00:49:19,911
Take care.

831
00:49:19,911 --> 00:49:21,901
That's happiness.

832
00:49:23,001 --> 00:49:26,441
That was a power move.

833
00:49:26,441 --> 00:49:27,921
Wow, so many.

834
00:49:27,921 --> 00:49:29,351
What do you think?

835
00:49:29,351 --> 00:49:31,471
You have to know when to spend.

836
00:49:31,471 --> 00:49:35,071
I tend to shop moderately.

837
00:49:35,071 --> 00:49:37,551
- Thank you so much.
- Aren't I the best?

838
00:49:37,551 --> 00:49:39,041
You're the best.

839
00:49:39,881 --> 00:49:43,251
- Let everyone see them.
- Like this?

840
00:49:43,251 --> 00:49:44,651
[Showing off]

841
00:49:45,901 --> 00:49:47,281
She can't stop giggling.

842
00:49:47,281 --> 00:49:49,051
- Should we go in?
- Yes.

843
00:49:49,051 --> 00:49:51,031
What? Daebak.

844
00:49:51,951 --> 00:49:53,031
Go in.

845
00:49:53,031 --> 00:49:54,811
- Hello.
- Hello.

846
00:49:54,811 --> 00:49:59,051
[An izakaya in Gwangjin-gu]

847
00:50:00,881 --> 00:50:02,461
They're sitting side by side.

848
00:50:02,461 --> 00:50:04,091
What would you like?

849
00:50:05,081 --> 00:50:06,411
There's a lot, right?

850
00:50:06,411 --> 00:50:09,621
- When you choose...
- Are you good at choosing dishes?

851
00:50:09,621 --> 00:50:11,151
I am.

852
00:50:11,151 --> 00:50:13,701
I'm not so good at it.

853
00:50:13,701 --> 00:50:18,001
I'll read the menu. Let's choose
based on your reaction.

854
00:50:19,281 --> 00:50:22,441
You don't like this that much.

855
00:50:24,181 --> 00:50:26,421
Do you not eat mackerel?

856
00:50:26,421 --> 00:50:27,621
No.

857
00:50:27,621 --> 00:50:30,321
- Roasted pork jowl?
- Roasted pork jowl?

858
00:50:30,321 --> 00:50:33,251
Pasta? Pork belly?

859
00:50:34,381 --> 00:50:35,571
Not bad.

860
00:50:35,571 --> 00:50:37,951
It's nice how he keeps looking at her.

861
00:50:37,951 --> 00:50:40,221
Fried shrimp?

862
00:50:40,221 --> 00:50:42,171
You don't like shrimp.

863
00:50:42,171 --> 00:50:44,051
Soft tofu and pork stir-fry?

864
00:50:44,051 --> 00:50:46,351
Soft tofu and pork stir-fry?

865
00:50:46,351 --> 00:50:48,511
- Sounds good.
- Take cilantros out?

866
00:50:48,511 --> 00:50:52,361
- I can eat cilantro.
- You do? I wasn't sure.

867
00:50:52,361 --> 00:50:56,561
Nos. 1, 2, and 3.

868
00:50:56,561 --> 00:50:59,571
- Sounds good.
- Let's order more if we want more.

869
00:50:59,571 --> 00:51:01,581
- What about a drink?
- Soju?

870
00:51:01,581 --> 00:51:03,911
Soju? Sounds good.

871
00:51:03,911 --> 00:51:05,851
Can we order now?

872
00:51:05,851 --> 00:51:09,001
Soft tofu and pork stir-fry
and a soju, please.

873
00:51:09,001 --> 00:51:11,781
He looks like soft tofu himself.

874
00:51:12,831 --> 00:51:15,151
This place is so cute.

875
00:51:15,151 --> 00:51:18,721
I've never been here. I've been meaning to.

876
00:51:18,721 --> 00:51:20,891
She's looking pretty, too.

877
00:51:21,771 --> 00:51:24,421
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

878
00:51:27,881 --> 00:51:29,801
I like the vibe.

879
00:51:34,621 --> 00:51:37,831
- It smells tasty.
- Totally.

880
00:51:39,771 --> 00:51:42,201
I'm shooting a mukbang.

881
00:51:42,201 --> 00:51:48,611
You act like you'll eat a lot
before you start eating.

882
00:51:48,611 --> 00:51:51,081
I actually eat a lot normally.

883
00:51:51,081 --> 00:51:53,921
How many packets of ramen can you eat?

884
00:51:53,921 --> 00:51:57,431
- I eat one and add rice later.
- That's pretty good. I do, too.

885
00:51:57,431 --> 00:52:00,091
One packet doesn't satisfy me these days.

886
00:52:00,091 --> 00:52:02,521
- You're a big eater.
- Of course.

887
00:52:02,521 --> 00:52:06,421
But you've been eating so little thus far.

888
00:52:06,421 --> 00:52:08,881
I have to watch my figure.

889
00:52:10,341 --> 00:52:14,661
- It's because I get puffy so easily.
- Really?

890
00:52:14,661 --> 00:52:17,631
- You don't seem like you do.
- I totally do.

891
00:52:18,521 --> 00:52:21,621
- My eyelids get...
- The eyelids?

892
00:52:21,621 --> 00:52:25,161
Yes, it's a bit sunken now, but...

893
00:52:25,161 --> 00:52:27,361
It sticks out?

894
00:52:27,361 --> 00:52:29,801
It's not that bad.

895
00:52:29,801 --> 00:52:32,311
It gets thick?

896
00:52:32,311 --> 00:52:34,041
Nice and thick.

897
00:52:34,041 --> 00:52:36,011
That's so nice.

898
00:52:39,511 --> 00:52:43,431
Whatever. I'll eat without
worrying about tomorrow.

899
00:52:43,431 --> 00:52:45,381
My skirt will burst, okay?

900
00:52:45,381 --> 00:52:48,421
The belt... I'll undo the belt.

901
00:52:48,421 --> 00:52:50,501
[Getting ready for a mukbang]

902
00:52:50,501 --> 00:52:53,481
We should've ordered one of each.

903
00:52:54,261 --> 00:52:56,221
Let's try eating first.

904
00:52:56,221 --> 00:52:58,911
We need to have the Dubai chocolate cookies.

905
00:52:58,911 --> 00:53:00,321
I'm so happy.

906
00:53:00,321 --> 00:53:03,621
Why am I so happy about the
Dubai chocolate cookies?

907
00:53:03,621 --> 00:53:05,161
How exciting.

908
00:53:07,961 --> 00:53:10,981
You're that excited about the
Dubai chocolate cookies?

909
00:53:10,981 --> 00:53:14,121
It's fun to buy something together.

910
00:53:14,121 --> 00:53:17,221
- So fun.
- Yes, it was really fun.

911
00:53:18,701 --> 00:53:23,031
[The dish was made while they were talking]

912
00:53:23,661 --> 00:53:26,131
Here's the tofu.

913
00:53:26,131 --> 00:53:28,051
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

914
00:53:28,051 --> 00:53:29,961
Looks delicious.

915
00:53:32,121 --> 00:53:34,191
Photo? Should we take photos?

916
00:53:34,191 --> 00:53:36,681
Right. Should we see who's worse at it?

917
00:53:36,681 --> 00:53:38,241
I'm excited.

918
00:53:38,241 --> 00:53:39,401
[Click]

919
00:53:39,401 --> 00:53:40,421
[Getting competitive]

920
00:53:41,021 --> 00:53:42,291
You won't show me?

921
00:53:42,291 --> 00:53:44,291
I'll show you after you take one.

922
00:53:44,291 --> 00:53:46,071
Let's see how bad you are.

923
00:53:46,071 --> 00:53:49,761
- It's already...
- It doesn't look right.

924
00:53:49,761 --> 00:53:52,091
It's not quite right.

925
00:53:52,091 --> 00:53:54,491
This is no good.

926
00:53:56,781 --> 00:53:59,491
You had to embarrass me like that?

927
00:53:59,491 --> 00:54:02,071
[After a photo battle]

928
00:54:03,651 --> 00:54:04,861
Cheers.

929
00:54:05,631 --> 00:54:07,271
Whoa.

930
00:54:12,551 --> 00:54:13,551
[Thumb up]

931
00:54:14,571 --> 00:54:17,481
- It's delicious.
- I know, right?

932
00:54:18,981 --> 00:54:20,931
- Do you approve?
- Yes.

933
00:54:21,851 --> 00:54:23,471
I love it.

934
00:54:24,281 --> 00:54:25,821
I'm happy.

935
00:54:26,821 --> 00:54:29,561
- Shishito pepper.
- Do you like it?

936
00:54:29,561 --> 00:54:31,091
- Of course.
- "Of course."

937
00:54:31,091 --> 00:54:32,391
Come on.

938
00:54:32,391 --> 00:54:34,041
Broccoli.

939
00:54:34,041 --> 00:54:36,551
- Of course.
- "Of course."

940
00:54:36,551 --> 00:54:38,501
[Smiling]

941
00:54:42,131 --> 00:54:43,281
[Gently]

942
00:54:49,221 --> 00:54:50,921
Did he touch her or not?

943
00:54:50,921 --> 00:54:53,931
Hey, hey, hey! Hey, hey, hey!

944
00:54:53,931 --> 00:54:55,401
What are you doing?

945
00:54:55,401 --> 00:54:59,951
It was hair. It was hair. That's okay.

946
00:54:59,951 --> 00:55:03,041
He didn't touch her skin.

947
00:55:08,031 --> 00:55:09,621
There you go.

948
00:55:13,191 --> 00:55:13,991
[Surprised]

949
00:55:13,991 --> 00:55:16,431
My gosh. Seriously.

950
00:55:16,431 --> 00:55:17,961
Do you go out a lot?

951
00:55:17,961 --> 00:55:20,321
No, I'm always home...

952
00:55:20,321 --> 00:55:22,781
- Just my regular spots.
- How about with friends?

953
00:55:22,781 --> 00:55:26,641
We go out. But we only go to the same spots.

954
00:55:26,641 --> 00:55:30,421
We go to the cafe and
to a restaurant. Stuff like that.

955
00:55:30,421 --> 00:55:32,271
You go to a cafe with friends?

956
00:55:32,271 --> 00:55:34,281
Yes, you don't?

957
00:55:34,281 --> 00:55:36,981
We go to cafes often.

958
00:55:36,981 --> 00:55:38,751
- Really?
- We go all the time.

959
00:55:38,751 --> 00:55:41,261
Really? Because you like cafes?

960
00:55:41,261 --> 00:55:44,261
Where else would you chat, then?

961
00:55:47,451 --> 00:55:49,771
Where do you hang out with your friends?

962
00:55:50,741 --> 00:55:52,721
- We don't go anywhere.
- You don't, right?

963
00:55:52,721 --> 00:55:55,301
I hang out at my friends' places.

964
00:55:55,301 --> 00:56:02,491
I want to try being with
someone who goes out often.

965
00:56:02,491 --> 00:56:05,101
Because I'll be out with him.

966
00:56:08,841 --> 00:56:11,481
- Do you like going for drives?
- I do.

967
00:56:11,481 --> 00:56:13,481
Should we go for a drive?

968
00:56:13,481 --> 00:56:15,241
While listening to music?

969
00:56:16,561 --> 00:56:17,821
That was major.

970
00:56:17,821 --> 00:56:19,451
With takeout food?

971
00:56:19,451 --> 00:56:22,041
Yes. I'd love that. While listening...

972
00:56:22,041 --> 00:56:25,871
To music? It'd be so nice.

973
00:56:26,761 --> 00:56:30,391
Not at a regular volume.

974
00:56:30,391 --> 00:56:33,231
I want it super loud.

975
00:56:33,231 --> 00:56:34,611
Me, too.

976
00:56:34,611 --> 00:56:36,751
I like listening to music in the car.

977
00:56:36,751 --> 00:56:41,381
I play music as soon as I get
in the car on my commute.

978
00:56:41,381 --> 00:56:45,541
Me, too. I play the music
on my way to the car.

979
00:56:45,541 --> 00:56:46,531
[Covering her arm]

980
00:56:47,211 --> 00:56:50,971
When you're crossing a bridge in the evening,

981
00:56:50,971 --> 00:56:56,161
a song suddenly feels different at times.

982
00:56:56,161 --> 00:57:00,081
I put that at the top of my list.

983
00:57:02,091 --> 00:57:04,191
I like music.

984
00:57:04,191 --> 00:57:07,611
I... No, that's embarrassing.

985
00:57:08,731 --> 00:57:11,231
I listen to music really loudly.

986
00:57:11,231 --> 00:57:14,621
I get so excited and scream.

987
00:57:15,461 --> 00:57:19,221
- So cute.
- Because you feel overwhelmed?

988
00:57:20,121 --> 00:57:21,791
Later on...

989
00:57:21,791 --> 00:57:25,521
- Sing for me.
- No, no, no.

990
00:57:25,521 --> 00:57:28,071
I'll share the song I like.

991
00:57:28,071 --> 00:57:30,921
- Let's listen to it together.
- Sounds good.

992
00:57:30,921 --> 00:57:35,981
[The two of them are making promises tonight]

993
00:57:40,271 --> 00:57:41,401
Do you like suyuk?

994
00:57:41,401 --> 00:57:42,841
[Nodding]

995
00:57:45,841 --> 00:57:47,611
- You don't have to eat it.
- He knows she dislikes it.

996
00:57:47,611 --> 00:57:49,761
Why? Could you tell?

997
00:57:49,761 --> 00:57:51,511
I'm finding out.

998
00:57:51,511 --> 00:57:53,971
I check your expressions each time.

999
00:57:55,031 --> 00:57:57,101
I could tell you don't like it.

1000
00:57:58,141 --> 00:57:59,931
I'm easy to read, huh?

1001
00:58:00,891 --> 00:58:02,931
Of course.

1002
00:58:02,931 --> 00:58:05,401
I can read you.

1003
00:58:07,961 --> 00:58:09,861
But you're tricky sometimes.

1004
00:58:10,991 --> 00:58:12,561
How about me?

1005
00:58:13,501 --> 00:58:15,261
- Can I read you?
- Yes.

1006
00:58:16,211 --> 00:58:17,871
Am I easy to read?

1007
00:58:19,501 --> 00:58:21,571
You aren't.

1008
00:58:21,571 --> 00:58:23,251
I'm not?

1009
00:58:24,251 --> 00:58:25,971
You aren't.

1010
00:58:27,451 --> 00:58:29,121
Really?

1011
00:58:30,171 --> 00:58:31,941
I can't really tell.

1012
00:58:34,841 --> 00:58:35,901
[Nodding]

1013
00:58:38,241 --> 00:58:41,091
Yu Gyeong is hopeless now.

1014
00:58:41,091 --> 00:58:43,181
She's in trouble.

1015
00:58:43,181 --> 00:58:44,391
That was too powerful.

1016
00:58:44,391 --> 00:58:46,601
For women in their early 20s...

1017
00:58:46,601 --> 00:58:49,621
- She needs to play hard to get.
- That's too hard for her.

1018
00:58:49,621 --> 00:58:52,071
She should hold back and play hard to get.

1019
00:58:57,831 --> 00:58:59,841
I'm a little sad.

1020
00:58:59,841 --> 00:59:02,961
Why? You don't want to go home?

1021
00:59:02,961 --> 00:59:04,451
I don't know.

1022
00:59:09,461 --> 00:59:12,831
[Her feelings keep showing through]

1023
00:59:12,831 --> 00:59:14,521
You eat well.

1024
00:59:15,401 --> 00:59:17,271
I'm happy.

1025
00:59:17,271 --> 00:59:21,561
[Their first date is coming to an end]

1026
00:59:23,841 --> 00:59:25,271
Gosh.

1027
00:59:25,271 --> 00:59:27,601
She doesn't want to go home. That's so...

1028
00:59:27,601 --> 00:59:29,921
"I want to drink. I don't want to go home."

1029
00:59:29,921 --> 00:59:32,991
- "I want to stay with you."
- What do we do?

1030
00:59:32,991 --> 00:59:34,401
Should we get bungeoppang?

1031
00:59:34,401 --> 00:59:37,791
- Yes, we have to.
- That place earlier?

1032
00:59:37,791 --> 00:59:39,581
- Three?
- 2,000 won for three.

1033
00:59:39,581 --> 00:59:41,191
We'll have three.

1034
00:59:41,191 --> 00:59:43,201
- Three?
- Yes.

1035
00:59:43,201 --> 00:59:45,501
Thank you.

1036
00:59:49,351 --> 00:59:52,021
- Do you like stuff like this?
- Daebak.

1037
00:59:52,021 --> 00:59:53,401
Mm!

1038
00:59:54,221 --> 00:59:56,361
So crispy, right?

1039
00:59:56,361 --> 00:59:57,921
[Planning their trip back]

1040
00:59:57,921 --> 01:00:01,481
Go home, stop by the store, and go back home?

1041
01:00:01,481 --> 01:00:03,901
- Want to stop by the store?
- Let's.

1042
01:00:03,901 --> 01:00:06,331
You want to buy something?

1043
01:00:06,331 --> 01:00:08,141
- What was I going to get?
- Soju.

1044
01:00:08,141 --> 01:00:09,861
Oh, right.

1045
01:00:09,861 --> 01:00:11,231
What else?

1046
01:00:11,231 --> 01:00:12,281
[Squint]

1047
01:00:15,451 --> 01:00:17,361
[Hesitant]

1048
01:00:18,931 --> 01:00:23,031
I kind of want to...

1049
01:00:25,921 --> 01:00:30,031
- talk to you casually.
- What? Go ahead.

1050
01:00:30,031 --> 01:00:32,181
- Do you want that? Is that okay?
- Yes.

1051
01:00:32,181 --> 01:00:33,531
Really?

1052
01:00:33,531 --> 01:00:36,301
If you do, I'll also...

1053
01:00:38,341 --> 01:00:40,141
I won't talk to you casually, but...

1054
01:00:40,141 --> 01:00:43,021
- I'd like you to.
- Really?

1055
01:00:43,021 --> 01:00:45,831
- Do you prefer that?
- Yes.

1056
01:00:45,831 --> 01:00:48,491
It depends on the person, but...

1057
01:00:48,491 --> 01:00:51,991
Want to talk casually?

1058
01:00:51,991 --> 01:00:54,241
- Should we talk casually?
- Should we?

1059
01:00:54,241 --> 01:00:55,631
- Should we?
- Yes?

1060
01:00:55,631 --> 01:00:57,281
Are they doing that now?

1061
01:01:01,271 --> 01:01:03,801
- Okay, let's talk casually.
- Sounds good.

1062
01:01:05,741 --> 01:01:09,021
- You think I look better with bangs?
- Yeah, I do.

1063
01:01:09,021 --> 01:01:10,311
Really?

1064
01:01:10,311 --> 01:01:13,391
- Does my hair look okay today?
- Yes.

1065
01:01:13,391 --> 01:01:17,461
But you've always...

1066
01:01:18,821 --> 01:01:22,621
looked nice, I think.

1067
01:01:25,151 --> 01:01:26,721
[Smiling]

1068
01:01:26,721 --> 01:01:27,981
[Smiling]

1069
01:01:27,981 --> 01:01:30,281
- Gosh.
- She loves him.

1070
01:01:30,281 --> 01:01:37,211
[A day full of unexpected joy]

1071
01:01:37,211 --> 01:01:40,931
She surrendered the moment
she confirmed it was Wu Yeol.

1072
01:01:40,931 --> 01:01:43,141
I can't forget her face then.

1073
01:01:43,141 --> 01:01:46,811
She feels conflicted.

1074
01:01:46,811 --> 01:01:49,491
She likes him, but she's worried, too.

1075
01:01:49,491 --> 01:01:53,441
Her plan to appear cool failed immediately.

1076
01:01:53,441 --> 01:01:57,221
She's a total baby in front of her crush.

1077
01:01:57,221 --> 01:01:58,921
My heart aches.

1078
01:01:58,921 --> 01:02:03,131
And most importantly, her hair. Her hair.

1079
01:02:03,131 --> 01:02:05,061
He could've said, "You got something here."

1080
01:02:05,061 --> 01:02:06,301
[But he did this instead]

1081
01:02:06,301 --> 01:02:10,291
- Couldn't he use a lint roller?
- Why would he do that?

1082
01:02:10,291 --> 01:02:12,381
[Clean her up with a lint roller?]

1083
01:02:12,381 --> 01:02:16,051
You're so touchy when it comes to Wu Yeol.

1084
01:02:16,051 --> 01:02:18,911
- He's sweet.
- Why are you so negative?

1085
01:02:18,911 --> 01:02:20,971
I think it's jealousy. I must be jealous.

1086
01:02:20,971 --> 01:02:25,471
Most men aren't able to do that like Wu Yeol.

1087
01:02:25,471 --> 01:02:27,961
I think it comes naturally to him.

1088
01:02:27,961 --> 01:02:30,791
- I don't think he practiced it.
- Absolutely not.

1089
01:02:30,791 --> 01:02:35,111
When she said she was hoping it was him,

1090
01:02:35,111 --> 01:02:40,151
she started curling up and turning red.

1091
01:02:40,151 --> 01:02:44,021
Most men wouldn't know what to do, either.

1092
01:02:44,021 --> 01:02:46,701
- But he was like, "Are you nervous?"
- Are you nervous?

1093
01:02:46,701 --> 01:02:48,101
He was so nonchalant.

1094
01:02:48,101 --> 01:02:49,841
He's seen it a million times.

1095
01:02:49,841 --> 01:02:51,861
What stood out to me earlier was...

1096
01:02:51,861 --> 01:02:53,851
When you look at the menu together,

1097
01:02:53,851 --> 01:02:57,341
you're like, "What do you want?
No. 3 and No. 2?"

1098
01:02:57,341 --> 01:03:00,821
But he turned toward her and
made eye contact. We should learn.

1099
01:03:00,821 --> 01:03:03,751
- You can't learn, everyone.
- It's not something you learn.

1100
01:03:03,751 --> 01:03:06,421
You have to be good-looking like him.

1101
01:03:06,421 --> 01:03:09,121
- Of course.
- Just because that looks cool,

1102
01:03:09,121 --> 01:03:11,381
and you stare at someone like this...

1103
01:03:11,381 --> 01:03:12,211
[Understood]

1104
01:03:12,211 --> 01:03:15,041
- It might backfire.
- It might get scary.

1105
01:03:15,041 --> 01:03:16,311
He's cool.

1106
01:03:16,311 --> 01:03:18,761
- Admit that.
- I admit it.

1107
01:03:18,761 --> 01:03:20,771
He's something else.

1108
01:03:23,451 --> 01:03:27,721
[Min Ju is waiting for someone]

1109
01:03:31,311 --> 01:03:33,791
Let me try to guess.

1110
01:03:33,791 --> 01:03:36,951
This is Seong Min's.

1111
01:03:36,951 --> 01:03:40,001
What was it? What were the contents?

1112
01:03:40,001 --> 01:03:45,651
I thought we'd cross paths
if it's meant to be

1113
01:03:46,581 --> 01:03:48,331
but I'm not sure.

1114
01:03:50,311 --> 01:03:54,061
I was attracted to him because
we had a good conversation.

1115
01:03:55,481 --> 01:03:57,111
Should we go together, then?

1116
01:03:57,111 --> 01:04:01,831
But I realized he might not
have felt the same way.

1117
01:04:03,071 --> 01:04:06,851
[Who should she want to see?]

1118
01:04:11,031 --> 01:04:13,541
[Nervous]

1119
01:04:14,121 --> 01:04:17,411
[Someone's approaching her from a distance]

1120
01:04:17,921 --> 01:04:19,801
Is it Seong Min?

1121
01:04:20,921 --> 01:04:22,531
My gosh.

1122
01:04:22,531 --> 01:04:26,371
Min Ju has never felt this way before.

1123
01:04:26,371 --> 01:04:31,421
[She doesn't know what to do]

1124
01:04:31,941 --> 01:04:34,951
- He's coming.
- He looks happy.

1125
01:04:35,751 --> 01:04:38,531
It's him. It was Seong Min.

1126
01:04:38,531 --> 01:04:40,931
She can't hide her feelings.

1127
01:04:40,931 --> 01:04:44,291
[Her date is Seong Min]

1128
01:04:45,221 --> 01:04:46,781
What?

1129
01:04:49,181 --> 01:04:52,131
I thought he and I had something.

1130
01:04:53,531 --> 01:04:57,551
I hope it's not the same Seong Min
I drove to Yeongjongdo with today.

1131
01:04:58,551 --> 01:05:00,351
I'm not sure. I guess I was too disappointed.

1132
01:05:00,351 --> 01:05:04,411
I just hope it's not him.
I want it to be someone else.

1133
01:05:09,121 --> 01:05:11,051
[Smiling]

1134
01:05:11,051 --> 01:05:14,851
That's when I started believing in fate.

1135
01:05:15,811 --> 01:05:18,291
I could tell it's you from a distance.

1136
01:05:20,001 --> 01:05:22,461
When he was walking toward me
from a distance,

1137
01:05:23,311 --> 01:05:25,821
I thought, "He and I
have something going on."

1138
01:05:25,821 --> 01:05:29,051
- She's fallen into fate theory alone.
- That's enough!

1139
01:05:29,051 --> 01:05:31,221
Hi.

1140
01:05:32,151 --> 01:05:33,901
Aren't you cold?

1141
01:05:33,901 --> 01:05:35,721
I'm cold.

1142
01:05:35,721 --> 01:05:37,491
- Give me your hand.
- What is it?

1143
01:05:37,491 --> 01:05:38,821
- Here.
- Really?

1144
01:05:38,821 --> 01:05:40,251
- What?
- That's so romantic.

1145
01:05:40,251 --> 01:05:43,011
- I saw you from far away.
- Me?

1146
01:05:45,551 --> 01:05:50,381
[A bookstore in Seoul]

1147
01:05:50,381 --> 01:05:52,821
They went to a bookstore.

1148
01:05:52,821 --> 01:05:55,291
[A huge library in the middle of the city]

1149
01:05:55,291 --> 01:05:57,141
Didn't you choose this place?

1150
01:05:57,141 --> 01:05:59,631
I've been wanting to come here.

1151
01:05:59,631 --> 01:06:01,651
I didn't know it was this big.

1152
01:06:04,621 --> 01:06:06,331
- Do you like going to bookstores?
- Yes.

1153
01:06:06,331 --> 01:06:07,971
- Really?
- I go to Kyobo Bookstore often.

1154
01:06:07,971 --> 01:06:10,081
- Really?
- Yes.

1155
01:06:10,081 --> 01:06:12,651
I think I go at least once a month.

1156
01:06:13,461 --> 01:06:18,111
I like reading,
but I like collecting books, too.

1157
01:06:18,111 --> 01:06:19,361
The smell of books.

1158
01:06:19,361 --> 01:06:21,781
- You can smell it.
- The new book smell.

1159
01:06:21,781 --> 01:06:23,111
- The paper smell.
- The paper smell.

1160
01:06:23,111 --> 01:06:24,451
Gosh, this couple is nice, too.

1161
01:06:24,451 --> 01:06:26,421
- Should we pick one?
- Sounds good.

1162
01:06:26,421 --> 01:06:28,971
[Picking a book for each other]

1163
01:06:28,971 --> 01:06:31,411
Picking a book for each other is great.

1164
01:06:31,411 --> 01:06:33,301
[Careful]

1165
01:06:33,301 --> 01:06:38,251
[Looking all around the bookstore]

1166
01:06:39,691 --> 01:06:41,001
I'm rich in books.

1167
01:06:41,001 --> 01:06:43,271
- What do we do?
- Three books in one day?

1168
01:06:43,271 --> 01:06:46,421
Let's do this instead.

1169
01:06:46,421 --> 01:06:49,931
[Buying the books to gift each other]

1170
01:06:55,531 --> 01:06:56,691
[A restaurant in Gangnam-gu]

1171
01:06:56,691 --> 01:06:58,351
Here.

1172
01:07:00,611 --> 01:07:02,511
How did you find this place?

1173
01:07:02,511 --> 01:07:04,991
I've been wanting to come here.
It's pretty here.

1174
01:07:04,991 --> 01:07:07,451
Yes, it's so pretty.

1175
01:07:13,411 --> 01:07:14,741
[Approaching]

1176
01:07:15,861 --> 01:07:17,031
- Thank you.
- I can hang it here, right?

1177
01:07:17,031 --> 01:07:20,001
- What's the deal?
- Great vibe.

1178
01:07:23,201 --> 01:07:25,381
[Smiling]

1179
01:07:25,381 --> 01:07:27,461
How nice.

1180
01:07:27,461 --> 01:07:29,261
There are so many plants here.

1181
01:07:29,261 --> 01:07:33,081
I think that's... I don't know.

1182
01:07:33,081 --> 01:07:36,121
I'll make sure to eat a lot today.

1183
01:07:36,121 --> 01:07:38,201
Let's.

1184
01:07:38,201 --> 01:07:40,171
I felt hungry the moment we came in.

1185
01:07:40,171 --> 01:07:41,881
I know, right?

1186
01:07:41,881 --> 01:07:44,411
I want to eat a lot of carbs.

1187
01:07:44,411 --> 01:07:46,851
You want a lot of carbs?

1188
01:07:46,851 --> 01:07:48,991
- Then...
- Like...

1189
01:07:48,991 --> 01:07:52,471
- pasta and...
- I want a risotto, too.

1190
01:07:53,481 --> 01:07:55,791
I'm so excited about the salad.

1191
01:07:55,791 --> 01:07:58,641
You said you don't like... What was it?

1192
01:07:59,791 --> 01:08:02,791
You like hard-boiled eggs,
but not chicken breast.

1193
01:08:02,791 --> 01:08:04,921
You have a good memory.

1194
01:08:04,921 --> 01:08:09,421
- Why get her excited by remembering?
- That makes her fall for him.

1195
01:08:09,421 --> 01:08:11,851
Should we look at the books now?

1196
01:08:11,851 --> 01:08:15,591
What? We need to give them to each other.

1197
01:08:16,801 --> 01:08:20,611
I thought of one book earlier.

1198
01:08:20,611 --> 01:08:24,361
I didn't think I'd end up with so many.

1199
01:08:24,361 --> 01:08:26,671
I'm so excited.

1200
01:08:26,671 --> 01:08:29,221
What's this bookmark?

1201
01:08:29,221 --> 01:08:32,421
- I put it in there.
- You're so annoying.

1202
01:08:37,151 --> 01:08:39,151
Min Ju is feeling happy immediately.

1203
01:08:39,151 --> 01:08:41,091
Thank you.

1204
01:08:41,091 --> 01:08:43,491
You want to wipe it first?

1205
01:08:43,491 --> 01:08:45,031
Do you always do that?

1206
01:08:45,031 --> 01:08:48,061
Dust collects on the top here.

1207
01:08:49,001 --> 01:08:50,411
It's dirty.

1208
01:08:51,201 --> 01:08:53,521
Thank you.

1209
01:08:53,521 --> 01:08:56,951
- What a good-looking couple.
- We're silly.

1210
01:08:56,951 --> 01:08:59,061
We said we'd talk casually.

1211
01:08:59,061 --> 01:09:02,681
- Should we talk casually?
- Try again? Okay.

1212
01:09:03,781 --> 01:09:06,751
[Chicken breast salad came out]

1213
01:09:07,361 --> 01:09:08,821
What do you think?

1214
01:09:11,281 --> 01:09:13,231
Is it good?

1215
01:09:13,231 --> 01:09:16,071
It must be really good.

1216
01:09:16,071 --> 01:09:18,371
[No need to explain]

1217
01:09:20,041 --> 01:09:20,821
[Tasty]

1218
01:09:20,821 --> 01:09:22,421
So charming.

1219
01:09:29,151 --> 01:09:30,791
It's good.

1220
01:09:30,791 --> 01:09:34,511
It lifts your spirits so you can eat more.

1221
01:09:38,811 --> 01:09:41,561
I really like the atmosphere here.

1222
01:09:41,561 --> 01:09:43,011
[Agree]

1223
01:09:46,471 --> 01:09:50,041
- I noticed something just now.
- What is it?

1224
01:09:50,041 --> 01:09:51,561
[Curious]

1225
01:09:51,561 --> 01:09:53,051
Can I tell you?

1226
01:09:53,051 --> 01:09:54,321
Yes.

1227
01:09:54,321 --> 01:09:57,411
When you empathize strongly...

1228
01:09:57,411 --> 01:09:59,311
- Don't tell me.
- Should I not?

1229
01:09:59,311 --> 01:10:02,291
- What is it?
- It's not a bad thing. It's like a habit.

1230
01:10:02,291 --> 01:10:04,581
[Nervous]

1231
01:10:04,581 --> 01:10:08,291
I noticed it earlier and yesterday, too.

1232
01:10:08,291 --> 01:10:10,541
You have an expressive face.

1233
01:10:10,541 --> 01:10:14,121
Very expressive. It's nice.
It's not a bad thing. It's nice.

1234
01:10:14,121 --> 01:10:18,301
- Right, like a cartoon character.
- What do I react when I'm surprised?

1235
01:10:18,301 --> 01:10:20,191
Your eyebrows curl and...

1236
01:10:20,191 --> 01:10:22,961
[Eyebrows?]

1237
01:10:23,711 --> 01:10:25,351
Something like this.

1238
01:10:25,351 --> 01:10:27,251
"Oh." Like this?

1239
01:10:28,591 --> 01:10:31,041
- Do I do that?
- Don't worry.

1240
01:10:31,041 --> 01:10:33,821
I meant it as a good thing.

1241
01:10:33,821 --> 01:10:36,061
- I think so.
- You're very expressive.

1242
01:10:36,061 --> 01:10:39,461
I don't think my face is that expressive.

1243
01:10:39,461 --> 01:10:42,331
- It is.
- Is it? Really? I didn't know.

1244
01:10:42,331 --> 01:10:44,081
He likes to analyze people.

1245
01:10:44,081 --> 01:10:46,681
We don't know much about ourselves.

1246
01:10:46,681 --> 01:10:48,191
You're right.

1247
01:10:50,021 --> 01:10:53,551
We don't know how we feel
and how others feel.

1248
01:10:53,551 --> 01:10:55,491
Clueless. That's the answer.

1249
01:10:55,491 --> 01:11:00,391
- She wants to know.
- You're clueless about how she feels.

1250
01:11:00,391 --> 01:11:02,471
I like comments like that.

1251
01:11:04,291 --> 01:11:06,511
Wu Yeol and I both agreed yesterday

1252
01:11:06,511 --> 01:11:09,631
that it's hard to make a decision yet.

1253
01:11:09,631 --> 01:11:11,211
What decision?

1254
01:11:11,211 --> 01:11:13,351
About how we feel.

1255
01:11:13,351 --> 01:11:15,991
Yes, of course.

1256
01:11:15,991 --> 01:11:19,011
It's hard to decide how we feel.

1257
01:11:20,881 --> 01:11:22,811
What I was worried about at first...

1258
01:11:22,811 --> 01:11:26,011
My biggest worry was
whether I'd develop feelings.

1259
01:11:26,011 --> 01:11:28,231
- I worried about that.
- Really?

1260
01:11:28,231 --> 01:11:32,031
Could I fall for someone within a month?

1261
01:11:32,031 --> 01:11:34,461
In such a short window?

1262
01:11:35,391 --> 01:11:37,941
I was worried about that.

1263
01:11:37,941 --> 01:11:41,071
But at some point...

1264
01:11:49,661 --> 01:11:53,551
[He suddenly developed feelings]

1265
01:11:53,551 --> 01:11:55,211
[Nodding]

1266
01:11:56,301 --> 01:11:58,931
- She's upset right now.
- What do you think?

1267
01:11:58,931 --> 01:12:01,191
You're the opposite of me.

1268
01:12:03,011 --> 01:12:05,941
- You're my polar opposite.
- Am I?

1269
01:12:05,941 --> 01:12:09,221
- Why do we keep talking formally?
- Right.

1270
01:12:10,451 --> 01:12:12,141
- Me?
- Yes.

1271
01:12:14,451 --> 01:12:17,091
- It's a secret.
- Okay, okay.

1272
01:12:17,091 --> 01:12:19,931
I expected that. Okay.

1273
01:12:23,691 --> 01:12:25,631
I like a secret.

1274
01:12:25,631 --> 01:12:27,171
What do we do?

1275
01:12:27,171 --> 01:12:32,851
[She's just stabbing the salad]

1276
01:12:32,851 --> 01:12:36,891
Min Ju started noticing that
he's not thrilled right now.

1277
01:12:36,891 --> 01:12:40,071
- Right.
- Even though they're talking smoothly.

1278
01:12:43,651 --> 01:12:47,231
[Poking]

1279
01:12:47,231 --> 01:12:49,881
- You're tired, aren't you?
- Me? Am I tired?

1280
01:12:49,881 --> 01:12:51,731
- Aren't you?
- No.

1281
01:12:51,731 --> 01:12:52,831
Sorry.

1282
01:12:52,831 --> 01:12:56,291
- Why? Do my eyes look tired?
- You look a little sleepy.

1283
01:12:56,291 --> 01:12:58,391
I'm not.

1284
01:12:58,391 --> 01:13:01,381
- I'm just feeling relaxed.
- Really?

1285
01:13:01,381 --> 01:13:04,921
- Am I not fun?
- You are. That's not it.

1286
01:13:04,921 --> 01:13:07,531
You're so bad at reading people.

1287
01:13:11,731 --> 01:13:16,981
For some reason,
I get sleepy when I'm nervous.

1288
01:13:16,981 --> 01:13:19,041
I get sleepy when I'm nervous.

1289
01:13:19,041 --> 01:13:24,491
When I argue with someone, I get sleepy.

1290
01:13:24,491 --> 01:13:26,611
- What? Really?
- Yes.

1291
01:13:27,741 --> 01:13:32,111
Like when I'm fighting
with my boyfriend or a friend.

1292
01:13:32,111 --> 01:13:34,081
I get sleepy at times like that.

1293
01:13:35,361 --> 01:13:38,341
That's why I'm not sleepy right now.

1294
01:13:40,881 --> 01:13:43,771
Everyone has complicated feelings.

1295
01:13:43,771 --> 01:13:47,021
I can't maintain a poker face.

1296
01:13:47,021 --> 01:13:51,041
My face keeps showing everything.

1297
01:13:51,041 --> 01:13:53,621
- I can feel it.
- You can?

1298
01:13:53,621 --> 01:13:58,861
So, I can sense that I'm getting flustered.

1299
01:13:58,861 --> 01:14:01,121
I just can't help it.

1300
01:14:02,491 --> 01:14:05,771
That could be a good thing, too.

1301
01:14:07,731 --> 01:14:09,461
Gosh.

1302
01:14:12,081 --> 01:14:13,521
I expected...

1303
01:14:13,521 --> 01:14:16,221
[Hehe]

1304
01:14:16,221 --> 01:14:19,321
You tried to make a joke, didn't you?

1305
01:14:20,381 --> 01:14:22,441
I think I joke a lot.

1306
01:14:22,441 --> 01:14:25,221
- Yes, it's fun.
- I joke a lot.

1307
01:14:25,221 --> 01:14:27,461
Me, too. I'm holding back right now.

1308
01:14:27,461 --> 01:14:30,571
Why don't you? Make me laugh now.

1309
01:14:31,551 --> 01:14:34,781
Was it this? Very good?

1310
01:14:34,781 --> 01:14:36,811
- Very good.
- Like this?

1311
01:14:36,811 --> 01:14:38,411
Very good.

1312
01:14:38,411 --> 01:14:40,401
Tastes very good.

1313
01:14:41,351 --> 01:14:43,681
I'll think about it before I go to bed.

1314
01:14:43,681 --> 01:14:45,761
Eat a lot, Seong Min.

1315
01:14:52,631 --> 01:14:56,451
[How is Min Ju feeling right now?]

1316
01:14:56,451 --> 01:15:01,721
- I think she got back on track a bit.
- She did.

1317
01:15:01,721 --> 01:15:05,141
That's reassuring me a bit.

1318
01:15:05,141 --> 01:15:09,501
They aren't getting super close,
but they're catching a breath.

1319
01:15:09,501 --> 01:15:12,751
She's taking one step at a time. That's good.

1320
01:15:12,751 --> 01:15:17,261
It's not that he's not interested,
but Yu Gyeong is his No. 1.

1321
01:15:17,261 --> 01:15:22,311
I thought things might get awkward,

1322
01:15:22,311 --> 01:15:26,841
but Min Ju seems to be enjoying the moment.

1323
01:15:26,841 --> 01:15:32,931
Their relationship
seems to have been repaired.

1324
01:15:32,931 --> 01:15:38,031
[She's walking fast while the sun is setting]

1325
01:15:38,031 --> 01:15:40,991
I hope Min Ju and Jun Hyeon work out.

1326
01:15:40,991 --> 01:15:43,061
I have a feeling they might.

1327
01:15:43,061 --> 01:15:46,001
[How will their date go?]

1328
01:15:48,201 --> 01:15:49,801
[Looking around]

1329
01:15:51,591 --> 01:15:55,521
Hello. It was you, Jun Hyeon.

1330
01:15:56,841 --> 01:15:58,881
Have a seat.

1331
01:16:01,871 --> 01:16:03,251
Where are you coming from?

1332
01:16:03,251 --> 01:16:05,711
I was on a date.

1333
01:16:05,711 --> 01:16:07,181
Are you having two dates today?

1334
01:16:07,181 --> 01:16:10,741
- Right. I'm going on two dates.
- I like that.

1335
01:16:12,041 --> 01:16:15,301
- You must've been busy since this morning.
- Yes, right.

1336
01:16:17,961 --> 01:16:21,501
Were you expecting to see someone?

1337
01:16:21,501 --> 01:16:23,691
I thought it might be you.

1338
01:16:23,691 --> 01:16:25,771
- Really?
- For no reason at all.

1339
01:16:25,771 --> 01:16:27,701
- Really?
- It was just a hunch.

1340
01:16:27,701 --> 01:16:30,411
- What's the deal?
- I thought it'd be you, too.

1341
01:16:30,411 --> 01:16:34,961
I thought "The Giving Tree" would be yours.

1342
01:16:34,961 --> 01:16:36,901
Really? Why?

1343
01:16:37,941 --> 01:16:42,561
I think it suits your MBTI type.

1344
01:16:42,561 --> 01:16:45,241
- You're an INFP, right?
- Yes.

1345
01:16:45,241 --> 01:16:47,651
I have a lot of INFPs around me.

1346
01:16:47,651 --> 01:16:50,881
- So are my close friends.
- Really?

1347
01:16:50,881 --> 01:16:55,141
So, I felt a connection.

1348
01:16:55,141 --> 01:16:56,821
- You've eaten, right?
- Yes.

1349
01:16:56,821 --> 01:16:59,621
Did you eat something good?
Is it a secret who you saw?

1350
01:16:59,621 --> 01:17:01,101
- Not allowed to say?
- I wonder.

1351
01:17:01,101 --> 01:17:03,081
- Who were you with?
- I'll tell you if I feel like it later.

1352
01:17:03,081 --> 01:17:05,001
Got it.

1353
01:17:05,001 --> 01:17:06,741
Have you eaten, then?

1354
01:17:06,741 --> 01:17:09,691
- I haven't.
- You haven't?

1355
01:17:09,691 --> 01:17:11,891
Oh, no...

1356
01:17:11,891 --> 01:17:16,621
- I'm hungry right now.
- You should eat after this, then.

1357
01:17:16,621 --> 01:17:20,071
[Desserts are ready]

1358
01:17:20,071 --> 01:17:23,861
Replenish blood sugar
since you haven't eaten.

1359
01:17:23,861 --> 01:17:26,081
I'm really hungry.

1360
01:17:27,811 --> 01:17:30,741
- Should I cut it for you?
- Thank you.

1361
01:17:30,741 --> 01:17:34,451
- How do you cut this?
- I know, right?

1362
01:17:34,451 --> 01:17:36,231
Do you like going to bakeries?

1363
01:17:36,231 --> 01:17:39,281
- It's not really my thing.
- It isn't?

1364
01:17:39,281 --> 01:17:43,521
- You like savory more than sweet.
- I'm more into savory.

1365
01:17:45,051 --> 01:17:46,291
Do you prefer sweet?

1366
01:17:46,291 --> 01:17:49,001
I prefer sweet these days.

1367
01:17:49,001 --> 01:17:52,451
- Why won't he look at her face?
- I like cakes.

1368
01:17:52,451 --> 01:17:55,031
- This is a cake, right?
- Yes. Looks like a sweet potato cake.

1369
01:17:55,031 --> 01:17:57,341
He's the opposite of Wu Yeol, isn't he?

1370
01:17:57,341 --> 01:17:58,511
[Mmm]

1371
01:17:58,511 --> 01:18:00,711
Men like that can be attractive, too.

1372
01:18:01,511 --> 01:18:07,061
I talked to Yu Gyeong
while driving yesterday.

1373
01:18:07,061 --> 01:18:09,461
Did you get to know Seong Min a lot?

1374
01:18:09,461 --> 01:18:11,831
- You drove together.
- While driving?

1375
01:18:11,831 --> 01:18:14,461
Yes, he's easy to talk to.

1376
01:18:16,021 --> 01:18:18,991
- He's very easy-going.
- Seong Min?

1377
01:18:18,991 --> 01:18:21,421
- Don't you think?
- He is.

1378
01:18:23,941 --> 01:18:28,481
- You can talk to him about anything, right?
- You're right.

1379
01:18:29,881 --> 01:18:32,251
We talked about all sorts of things.
About our hobbies,

1380
01:18:32,251 --> 01:18:35,121
the books and music we like.

1381
01:18:35,121 --> 01:18:37,531
Our dating style and how
many relationships we've had.

1382
01:18:37,531 --> 01:18:39,821
You talked about personal things?

1383
01:18:39,821 --> 01:18:42,751
All of these are personal.

1384
01:18:43,851 --> 01:18:47,671
- You talked about relationships, too.
- Right.

1385
01:18:50,721 --> 01:18:52,681
Have you been in many relationships?

1386
01:18:52,681 --> 01:18:54,791
What do you think?

1387
01:18:56,051 --> 01:18:58,951
- I don't think you've had that many.
- Really?

1388
01:18:58,951 --> 01:19:01,561
You're 27. I think...

1389
01:19:02,801 --> 01:19:04,811
maybe four?

1390
01:19:04,811 --> 01:19:07,061
Am I wrong?

1391
01:19:07,061 --> 01:19:09,921
- Four?
- You don't have to tell me.

1392
01:19:09,921 --> 01:19:12,251
- It's less than that.
- Really?

1393
01:19:12,251 --> 01:19:14,991
- I haven't had that many.
- Why? Just because?

1394
01:19:14,991 --> 01:19:17,881
Why haven't I?

1395
01:19:17,881 --> 01:19:20,091
Is work more important to you?

1396
01:19:20,091 --> 01:19:22,851
- Not at all.
- That's not why?

1397
01:19:25,161 --> 01:19:30,591
I think I'm used to being alone.

1398
01:19:30,591 --> 01:19:35,081
So, I've always been alone.

1399
01:19:36,641 --> 01:19:39,741
I thought you were active.
You enjoy physical activities.

1400
01:19:39,741 --> 01:19:41,261
Right. I'm active.

1401
01:19:41,261 --> 01:19:43,931
- You want to try skydiving.
- I do.

1402
01:19:43,931 --> 01:19:48,261
- But you like being alone, too?
- Yes, I enjoy stillness, too.

1403
01:19:49,221 --> 01:19:52,071
If you ask what my hobby is...

1404
01:19:53,521 --> 01:19:55,781
I think I just like being alone.

1405
01:19:55,781 --> 01:19:59,961
I walk or watch a movie alone.

1406
01:19:59,961 --> 01:20:01,591
Do you have a favorite movie?

1407
01:20:01,591 --> 01:20:03,881
Favorite movie?

1408
01:20:03,881 --> 01:20:06,351
"Soul?" You know that one?

1409
01:20:06,351 --> 01:20:07,801
I've heard of it.

1410
01:20:07,801 --> 01:20:11,011
- It's an animation.
- I love that one.

1411
01:20:11,011 --> 01:20:12,291
Do you have a favorite?

1412
01:20:12,291 --> 01:20:13,301
- Yes.
- What is it?

1413
01:20:13,301 --> 01:20:15,371
I like "Interstellar."

1414
01:20:15,371 --> 01:20:17,441
Wow, why?

1415
01:20:17,441 --> 01:20:19,381
When I watch it, feeling down,

1416
01:20:19,381 --> 01:20:24,591
I'm reminded that I'm just a speck
of dust in the universe.

1417
01:20:24,591 --> 01:20:28,141
I like movies around time and place.

1418
01:20:28,141 --> 01:20:32,281
Movies set in space.
I like "Inception." Like SF movies.

1419
01:20:32,281 --> 01:20:34,221
That's kind of surprising.

1420
01:20:34,221 --> 01:20:36,601
Really? You think so?

1421
01:20:37,481 --> 01:20:39,221
You said you're just a speck of dust.

1422
01:20:39,221 --> 01:20:43,461
I've never heard anyone
say that about "Interstellar."

1423
01:20:43,461 --> 01:20:44,881
You feel comforted by that?

1424
01:20:44,881 --> 01:20:47,941
Yes. I listen to the "Interstellar"
soundtrack when I'm down.

1425
01:20:47,941 --> 01:20:53,291
I turn on the noise-canceling and
listen to it with my eyes closed.

1426
01:20:53,291 --> 01:20:54,511
- You feel healed?
- Yes.

1427
01:20:54,511 --> 01:20:55,931
Daebak.

1428
01:20:55,931 --> 01:20:59,411
It's nice that you have something like that.

1429
01:20:59,411 --> 01:21:01,761
You feel healed immediately afterward?

1430
01:21:01,761 --> 01:21:06,091
Yes, when I felt down
at the Signal House, too.

1431
01:21:06,091 --> 01:21:09,011
Why did you feel down here?
What do you find stressful?

1432
01:21:09,011 --> 01:21:12,701
You can feel stressed
because of various situations.

1433
01:21:12,701 --> 01:21:15,411
I guess you don't feel any stress yet.

1434
01:21:15,411 --> 01:21:18,421
- I'm just so happy right now.
- Really?

1435
01:21:18,421 --> 01:21:19,481
[He moved in three days ago]

1436
01:21:19,481 --> 01:21:22,251
- He's not there yet.
- He could use a little stress.

1437
01:21:22,251 --> 01:21:24,941
- He's unexpectedly funny.
- I know.

1438
01:21:24,941 --> 01:21:27,801
He's such a funny character.

1439
01:21:28,661 --> 01:21:30,031
How nice.

1440
01:21:30,031 --> 01:21:32,191
Everyone is so nice.

1441
01:21:35,711 --> 01:21:37,421
- By the way...
- Yes.

1442
01:21:37,421 --> 01:21:40,301
You seem very outgoing.

1443
01:21:40,301 --> 01:21:41,881
- Do I?
- Yes.

1444
01:21:42,821 --> 01:21:45,851
- For an INFP?
- Yes.

1445
01:21:45,851 --> 01:21:48,051
- Gosh, thank you.
- Get in.

1446
01:21:48,051 --> 01:21:49,471
Thank you.

1447
01:21:49,471 --> 01:21:52,881
[Jun Hyeon opens the door for Min Ju]

1448
01:21:52,881 --> 01:21:54,761
Thank you.

1449
01:21:58,141 --> 01:22:01,021
- What perfume do you use?
- Mine is Tom Ford.

1450
01:22:01,021 --> 01:22:03,461
- I use a Tom Ford, too.
- Really?

1451
01:22:03,461 --> 01:22:05,541
This is mine.

1452
01:22:05,541 --> 01:22:10,431
- Huh? I love this. Let me smell it.
- Here's perfume again.

1453
01:22:10,431 --> 01:22:14,961
I'm into the androgynous scents lately.

1454
01:22:14,961 --> 01:22:19,451
I don't think I've met a woman
who uses Tom Ford perfumes.

1455
01:22:19,451 --> 01:22:20,951
Really?

1456
01:22:20,951 --> 01:22:24,021
The scent suits you so well.

1457
01:22:24,021 --> 01:22:27,241
- Could you smell it?
- I smelled it a bit in the car.

1458
01:22:27,241 --> 01:22:30,061
- Driving always makes me happy.
- Really?

1459
01:22:30,061 --> 01:22:31,931
Did you feel happy yesterday, too?

1460
01:22:31,931 --> 01:22:34,771
No, I mean, the thing is...

1461
01:22:34,771 --> 01:22:37,151
Some people don't like driving
for a long time.

1462
01:22:37,151 --> 01:22:40,171
I love it. I love going for drives.

1463
01:22:40,171 --> 01:22:42,161
Do you go for drives alone, too?

1464
01:22:42,161 --> 01:22:45,441
I have. I listened to music.

1465
01:22:45,441 --> 01:22:48,031
Seong Min and I are talking casually.

1466
01:22:48,031 --> 01:22:50,051
Really? Feel free to do that.

1467
01:22:50,051 --> 01:22:52,721
- I'd like that myself.
- Really?

1468
01:22:52,721 --> 01:22:54,101
Would that be okay?

1469
01:22:54,101 --> 01:22:56,561
- Why? What's your concern?
- You might not like it.

1470
01:22:56,561 --> 01:22:57,931
Oh, me?

1471
01:22:57,931 --> 01:23:02,971
I'd like to talk casually
since it'd bring us closer.

1472
01:23:02,971 --> 01:23:05,251
- Let's talk casually, then.
- The vibe is improving.

1473
01:23:05,251 --> 01:23:06,951
I wanted to do it sooner, but...

1474
01:23:06,951 --> 01:23:10,471
- Sounds good.
- But we didn't get a chance to talk.

1475
01:23:11,451 --> 01:23:14,761
- Have you been to Haebangchon?
- I don't come here often.

1476
01:23:14,761 --> 01:23:16,321
Oh, really?

1477
01:23:16,321 --> 01:23:19,411
It's nice here. I like the atmosphere.

1478
01:23:19,411 --> 01:23:21,191
Is this it?

1479
01:23:24,231 --> 01:23:26,491
Thank you.

1480
01:23:26,491 --> 01:23:29,351
Hello, hello.

1481
01:23:29,351 --> 01:23:30,991
Thank you.

1482
01:23:32,401 --> 01:23:37,161
- Meat. You wanted meat.
- I want protein.

1483
01:23:37,161 --> 01:23:40,421
- Did you have pasta for lunch?
- Yes.

1484
01:23:40,421 --> 01:23:42,031
Since you had pasta...

1485
01:23:42,031 --> 01:23:44,921
Sir, we'd like to order.

1486
01:23:45,921 --> 01:23:51,101
We'll have the calamari, iberico, and...

1487
01:23:51,101 --> 01:23:54,021
[Jun Hyeon is ordering for Min Ju]

1488
01:23:54,021 --> 01:23:55,621
Should I remove the wine glasses?

1489
01:23:55,621 --> 01:23:57,251
Yes, please.

1490
01:23:57,251 --> 01:24:01,121
- You don't drink wine. You can't drink.
- Right.

1491
01:24:02,331 --> 01:24:05,561
Cheers. Nice to meet you.

1492
01:24:08,951 --> 01:24:10,591
Wow.

1493
01:24:10,591 --> 01:24:13,291
- Squeeze the lime juice on it.
- Sounds good.

1494
01:24:13,291 --> 01:24:15,611
[The dishes are coming out one by one]

1495
01:24:19,051 --> 01:24:21,271
- It's so delicious.
- Is it?

1496
01:24:21,271 --> 01:24:23,541
I think I'll eat a lot here.

1497
01:24:23,541 --> 01:24:25,521
Eat more.

1498
01:24:25,521 --> 01:24:27,471
"Eat more."

1499
01:24:27,471 --> 01:24:31,091
He's like a husband. He's already a husband.

1500
01:24:31,091 --> 01:24:33,781
I like Jun Hyeon.

1501
01:24:33,781 --> 01:24:35,751
Eat more.

1502
01:24:35,751 --> 01:24:37,801
Would you like another pasta?

1503
01:24:37,801 --> 01:24:42,241
[She's really helping herself]

1504
01:24:42,241 --> 01:24:45,121
[Hehe]

1505
01:24:45,121 --> 01:24:47,591
Could we look at the menu?

1506
01:24:48,591 --> 01:24:50,951
We could have another dish at this rate.

1507
01:24:50,951 --> 01:24:55,161
- It's all so tasty.
- The tartare? You want that?

1508
01:24:55,161 --> 01:24:59,621
He's very attentive to the other person.

1509
01:24:59,621 --> 01:25:01,671
I found it attractive.

1510
01:25:01,671 --> 01:25:04,211
My heart fluttered
when he opened the car door.

1511
01:25:04,211 --> 01:25:10,241
It was extra nice
since he opened it so casually.

1512
01:25:10,241 --> 01:25:12,521
It wasn't like, "I should impress her."

1513
01:25:12,521 --> 01:25:17,271
It felt like he was doing it
out of good manners.

1514
01:25:17,271 --> 01:25:19,981
That got me excited.

1515
01:25:19,981 --> 01:25:21,911
He's quiet, but he's a straight shooter.

1516
01:25:21,911 --> 01:25:23,291
He's caring without showing off.

1517
01:25:23,291 --> 01:25:26,101
So, tell me about this, Oppa.

1518
01:25:26,101 --> 01:25:30,321
Why did you choose "The Giving Tree"?

1519
01:25:30,321 --> 01:25:33,091
It's cool. Without wanting anything,

1520
01:25:33,091 --> 01:25:36,801
it endlessly gives,
hoping the person is happy.

1521
01:25:36,801 --> 01:25:40,181
- I think that's what love is.
- Right.

1522
01:25:40,181 --> 01:25:43,961
But it gets taken advantage of in the end.

1523
01:25:43,961 --> 01:25:47,041
What do you think
of one-directional love like that?

1524
01:25:47,041 --> 01:25:49,541
Getting taken advantage of in the end?

1525
01:25:50,541 --> 01:25:57,831
I think it did that of its own
will rather than being used.

1526
01:25:57,831 --> 01:26:01,281
I never thought it was taken advantage of.

1527
01:26:01,281 --> 01:26:04,791
I think he said his MBTI was INFP.

1528
01:26:04,791 --> 01:26:08,291
That type has deep
and selective relationships.

1529
01:26:08,291 --> 01:26:13,721
They give endlessly once they
open up to someone. Like a tall tree.

1530
01:26:13,721 --> 01:26:18,361
I have many friends like that.
I thought he'd be like that, too.

1531
01:26:18,361 --> 01:26:20,391
Have you done that yourself?

1532
01:26:20,391 --> 01:26:23,881
Have you given endlessly?

1533
01:26:24,881 --> 01:26:26,341
I don't think I have.

1534
01:26:26,341 --> 01:26:28,621
I strive to do that.

1535
01:26:28,621 --> 01:26:31,781
- You want to give endlessly?
- I found it so impressive.

1536
01:26:31,781 --> 01:26:34,981
- That's a good answer.
- I like them talking casually.

1537
01:26:36,831 --> 01:26:40,861
Do you handle silence well?

1538
01:26:40,861 --> 01:26:43,701
- Yes.
- Really?

1539
01:26:44,851 --> 01:26:47,001
Can you not handle silence?

1540
01:26:47,001 --> 01:26:48,671
I like it, too.

1541
01:26:49,671 --> 01:26:52,871
- You said you like someone who is talkative.
- Yes.

1542
01:26:52,871 --> 01:26:55,691
What's the reason? Just because?

1543
01:26:55,691 --> 01:27:00,641
I'm bubbly on the outside, you know.

1544
01:27:00,641 --> 01:27:06,511
That's why I've been with quiet people.

1545
01:27:06,511 --> 01:27:14,631
That's why I want to be with someone fun now.

1546
01:27:15,821 --> 01:27:17,401
- Someone fun to talk to?
- Yes.

1547
01:27:17,401 --> 01:27:20,311
- You're tired of talking alone?
- Yes.

1548
01:27:20,311 --> 01:27:21,781
Conversations matter the most, right?

1549
01:27:21,781 --> 01:27:24,201
- Right? It's important.
- I value that the most.

1550
01:27:24,201 --> 01:27:25,231
Really?

1551
01:27:25,231 --> 01:27:27,021
I thought everyone was like that.

1552
01:27:27,021 --> 01:27:31,441
How do you date someone
if the conversation isn't fun?

1553
01:27:31,441 --> 01:27:35,471
It has to be fun to talk to each other.
The back and forth is crucial.

1554
01:27:35,471 --> 01:27:38,171
- And have a similar sense of humor, too.
- Right.

1555
01:27:38,171 --> 01:27:40,351
A sense of humor is so important.

1556
01:27:40,351 --> 01:27:43,491
[Glancing]

1557
01:27:46,941 --> 01:27:50,691
Don't you want to be the last ones
to get home?

1558
01:27:50,691 --> 01:27:52,941
Let's go for a drive.

1559
01:27:52,941 --> 01:27:54,521
Let's go.

1560
01:27:54,521 --> 01:27:56,371
Thanks for the meal.

1561
01:27:56,371 --> 01:27:58,881
- Walk inside.
- Thank you.

1562
01:27:58,881 --> 01:28:01,471
Wow, so caring.

1563
01:28:02,601 --> 01:28:06,161
I think I find older men easier to talk to.

1564
01:28:10,541 --> 01:28:12,481
We're here.

1565
01:28:12,481 --> 01:28:14,341
[Arriving at the Han River at night]

1566
01:28:14,341 --> 01:28:16,151
What a nice view.

1567
01:28:16,951 --> 01:28:20,111
- Where do you find joy in everyday life?
- Joy?

1568
01:28:20,111 --> 01:28:26,961
I don't take the subway.
I insist on taking the bus.

1569
01:28:26,961 --> 01:28:30,281
- I prefer the bus, too.
- Really?

1570
01:28:30,281 --> 01:28:33,661
I listen to music while on the bus.

1571
01:28:33,661 --> 01:28:36,601
I've gotten on a bus without a destination

1572
01:28:36,601 --> 01:28:39,491
because I like looking out the window,
listening to music.

1573
01:28:39,491 --> 01:28:40,911
- Really?
- I just drove.

1574
01:28:40,911 --> 01:28:42,961
Me, too. I've been on the bus to Everland.

1575
01:28:42,961 --> 01:28:49,921
I took the bus
to Everland from Ilsan and back.

1576
01:28:49,921 --> 01:28:52,221
- How crazy.
- It's really nice.

1577
01:28:52,221 --> 01:28:54,421
Right. It's so nice.

1578
01:28:54,421 --> 01:28:57,521
- Do you mind getting rained on?
- Getting rained on?

1579
01:28:57,521 --> 01:28:59,251
- Can you tolerate it?
- Yes.

1580
01:28:59,251 --> 01:29:01,721
- Say it's suddenly pouring rain.
- I love it.

1581
01:29:01,721 --> 01:29:04,141
You're in a store, but you have no umbrella.

1582
01:29:04,141 --> 01:29:08,081
The person you're with suggests
getting rained on. Can you do it?

1583
01:29:08,081 --> 01:29:09,801
- Yes.
- Really?

1584
01:29:09,801 --> 01:29:12,741
- You can't do it, huh?
- No, I really love it.

1585
01:29:12,741 --> 01:29:14,301
Really?

1586
01:29:14,301 --> 01:29:17,231
What's with him? How interesting.

1587
01:29:17,231 --> 01:29:18,981
He strives for freedom.

1588
01:29:18,981 --> 01:29:20,391
He's the type Min Ju likes.

1589
01:29:20,391 --> 01:29:23,141
- I like Jun Hyeon for her.
- Let's go.

1590
01:29:23,141 --> 01:29:26,741
It's disappointing when someone says no.

1591
01:29:26,741 --> 01:29:28,881
Why be disappointed?

1592
01:29:28,881 --> 01:29:31,701
- They just don't like it.
- It is disappointing.

1593
01:29:31,701 --> 01:29:36,641
We had more in common than I thought.

1594
01:29:36,641 --> 01:29:39,641
I thought he could be easy to be with.

1595
01:29:39,641 --> 01:29:42,121
They go well together.

1596
01:29:42,121 --> 01:29:45,891
Is my personality as you expected?

1597
01:29:45,891 --> 01:29:48,571
What do you think after talking to me today?

1598
01:29:51,071 --> 01:29:52,831
[Anticipation]

1599
01:29:55,011 --> 01:29:58,501
You're a bit different from what I expected.

1600
01:29:58,501 --> 01:30:00,841
In what way? How am I different?

1601
01:30:00,841 --> 01:30:07,981
I expected some aspects. I knew
you'd make people comfortable.

1602
01:30:07,981 --> 01:30:09,641
I thought...

1603
01:30:11,391 --> 01:30:15,721
I might not find it easy to talk to you.

1604
01:30:15,721 --> 01:30:17,261
He thought that?

1605
01:30:17,261 --> 01:30:21,871
You're easygoing, and you put people at ease,

1606
01:30:21,871 --> 01:30:27,161
but I didn't think we'd have much in common.

1607
01:30:27,161 --> 01:30:29,981
That's what he thought.

1608
01:30:29,981 --> 01:30:33,541
You're so upbeat.

1609
01:30:33,541 --> 01:30:39,021
I felt that upbeat people
tend to be insincere

1610
01:30:39,021 --> 01:30:42,371
once I start talking to them sometimes.

1611
01:30:42,371 --> 01:30:45,191
I know not everyone is like that.

1612
01:30:45,191 --> 01:30:47,641
But I've met people like that.

1613
01:30:47,641 --> 01:30:54,421
I wondered if we could
exchange sincere feelings.

1614
01:30:54,421 --> 01:30:56,941
I never thought of you negatively.

1615
01:30:58,151 --> 01:31:00,641
I didn't know much about you, to be honest.

1616
01:31:00,641 --> 01:31:02,741
He's saying she's not like that.

1617
01:31:02,741 --> 01:31:07,611
[Same conversation, different thoughts]

1618
01:31:08,211 --> 01:31:10,871
- I felt so shocked when I heard that.
- Why?

1619
01:31:10,871 --> 01:31:14,691
That's why I observe people for a long time.

1620
01:31:14,691 --> 01:31:17,011
I tend not to judge immediately.

1621
01:31:17,011 --> 01:31:19,341
He hasn't reached the conclusion.

1622
01:31:19,341 --> 01:31:24,001
I thought we had nice conversations.

1623
01:31:24,001 --> 01:31:25,731
But...

1624
01:31:26,671 --> 01:31:33,561
[Uncomfortable feeling is lingering]

1625
01:31:34,201 --> 01:31:37,831
- Should we get going? It's 12. Is that okay?
- Yes, let's go.

1626
01:31:39,881 --> 01:31:48,991
[How did this date affect their feelings?]

1627
01:31:48,991 --> 01:31:50,601
The last conversation has a lingering effect.

1628
01:31:50,601 --> 01:31:53,661
I know. It was going well. What happened?

1629
01:31:53,661 --> 01:31:56,391
It was so sad.
They were getting along so well.

1630
01:31:56,391 --> 01:32:00,731
Didn't they have a good vibe
before the miscommunication?

1631
01:32:00,731 --> 01:32:02,021
It was great.

1632
01:32:02,021 --> 01:32:03,651
She's hasty.

1633
01:32:03,651 --> 01:32:05,691
She judges too hastily.

1634
01:32:05,691 --> 01:32:07,931
They misunderstood each other.

1635
01:32:07,931 --> 01:32:10,871
Jun Hyeon tends to save his words.

1636
01:32:10,871 --> 01:32:14,301
I thought he'd say, "I was happy
we talked today," but he didn't.

1637
01:32:14,301 --> 01:32:16,921
He's shy. He can't be so direct.

1638
01:32:16,921 --> 01:32:19,251
He didn't have to. But why was she mistaken?

1639
01:32:19,251 --> 01:32:21,781
- When you say stuff like that...
- I don't get it.

1640
01:32:21,781 --> 01:32:26,821
he should've made it brief
about disliking upbeat people.

1641
01:32:26,821 --> 01:32:29,691
- But he talked about it for too long.
- He did.

1642
01:32:29,691 --> 01:32:32,051
- He said a bit too much.
- That's what he thought.

1643
01:32:32,051 --> 01:32:35,401
He should've said what he liked about her.

1644
01:32:35,401 --> 01:32:37,091
Based on how he talked...

1645
01:32:37,091 --> 01:32:39,471
- It's his fault.
- That's what I think.

1646
01:32:39,471 --> 01:32:40,761
I guess so.

1647
01:32:40,761 --> 01:32:44,111
You can tell from the way he talks.

1648
01:32:44,111 --> 01:32:46,761
He tends to cut to the chase.

1649
01:32:46,761 --> 01:32:49,241
He doesn't know
that she misunderstood, either.

1650
01:32:49,241 --> 01:32:52,791
- Right now, they're...
- Things went wrong.

1651
01:32:52,791 --> 01:32:59,261
From what we saw,
he was the sweetest and seemed excited.

1652
01:32:59,261 --> 01:33:03,411
But she thinks,
"Maybe we aren't on the same page."

1653
01:33:03,411 --> 01:33:06,851
She might've been mistaken.

1654
01:33:06,851 --> 01:33:08,671
Both hands full. How nice.

1655
01:33:08,671 --> 01:33:10,621
[Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong are
heading back to the house]

1656
01:33:10,621 --> 01:33:13,761
I know. Our hands are full.

1657
01:33:13,761 --> 01:33:15,881
[Both hands full, feeling good tonight]

1658
01:33:23,051 --> 01:33:25,121
Is your head hard, Oppa?

1659
01:33:25,121 --> 01:33:26,651
Is my head hard?

1660
01:33:26,651 --> 01:33:28,151
Want to try hitting it?

1661
01:33:28,151 --> 01:33:30,261
It's not.

1662
01:33:30,261 --> 01:33:32,881
No, it's not that.

1663
01:33:34,371 --> 01:33:37,571
Can't stop laughing, right?

1664
01:33:37,571 --> 01:33:38,901
We keep laughing.

1665
01:33:38,901 --> 01:33:40,741
Are you that happy?

1666
01:33:40,741 --> 01:33:41,871
Of course.

1667
01:33:41,871 --> 01:33:43,951
What? They're so sweet together.

1668
01:33:43,951 --> 01:33:46,371
They're so lovey-dovey.

1669
01:33:49,281 --> 01:33:51,601
[Looking]

1670
01:33:51,601 --> 01:33:53,041
Is anyone home?

1671
01:33:55,591 --> 01:33:57,571
We're the first.

1672
01:34:00,121 --> 01:34:02,991
Let's brag. Let's display it.

1673
01:34:02,991 --> 01:34:05,091
What we bought?

1674
01:34:08,691 --> 01:34:10,011
So cute.

1675
01:34:10,011 --> 01:34:11,191
- Daebak.
- Daebak.

1676
01:34:11,191 --> 01:34:13,051
- Should we take a photo?
- Crazy.

1677
01:34:13,051 --> 01:34:14,931
- Should we take a photo?
- Photo?

1678
01:34:15,881 --> 01:34:18,171
Ten Dubai chocolate cookies.

1679
01:34:20,281 --> 01:34:22,351
It's a heart shape.

1680
01:34:23,691 --> 01:34:26,161
Seong Min was done after lunch.

1681
01:34:26,161 --> 01:34:28,501
[Alone in the empty house]

1682
01:34:30,901 --> 01:34:35,211
[Lost in thoughts,
looking at everyone's books]

1683
01:34:35,921 --> 01:34:38,641
Feeling sorry for myself,

1684
01:34:38,641 --> 01:34:41,421
I ate the doenjang stew from two days ago.

1685
01:34:47,761 --> 01:34:51,181
I thought I might as well drink alone.

1686
01:34:51,181 --> 01:34:53,341
I drank the leftover takju.

1687
01:34:55,051 --> 01:34:57,101
[Spent a lonely evening]

1688
01:34:57,101 --> 01:34:58,901
[Dozing off]

1689
01:35:00,101 --> 01:35:01,721
[Swoosh]

1690
01:35:05,831 --> 01:35:06,811
[Glancing]

1691
01:35:08,041 --> 01:35:09,861
Wait. Hold on.

1692
01:35:09,861 --> 01:35:12,071
Let's leave this and go.

1693
01:35:12,071 --> 01:35:13,101
[Glancing]

1694
01:35:13,861 --> 01:35:16,961
Huh? What? Were you home?

1695
01:35:16,961 --> 01:35:19,811
- Why?
- I had one of the two dates.

1696
01:35:19,811 --> 01:35:21,461
You were one of the two?

1697
01:35:21,461 --> 01:35:23,551
I was like,

1698
01:35:23,551 --> 01:35:26,531
- "When will they be back?"
- Unni went on two dates.

1699
01:35:26,531 --> 01:35:28,101
Oh, you're right.

1700
01:35:28,101 --> 01:35:30,341
- They went on the first date.
- Oh, I see.

1701
01:35:30,341 --> 01:35:32,101
- He's leaving.
- Should we go upstairs?

1702
01:35:32,101 --> 01:35:33,481
Yes.

1703
01:35:36,781 --> 01:35:39,201
What? What's going on?

1704
01:35:39,201 --> 01:35:40,911
It was fun.

1705
01:35:40,911 --> 01:35:42,401
Did you have fun today?

1706
01:35:42,401 --> 01:35:43,971
Of course.

1707
01:35:43,971 --> 01:35:46,251
- Should we wait outside?
- Yes.

1708
01:35:46,251 --> 01:35:48,521
He can hear them giggling.

1709
01:35:48,521 --> 01:35:51,041
[Same space, different moods]

1710
01:35:51,831 --> 01:35:55,091
I was bothered to a certain extent.

1711
01:35:55,091 --> 01:35:59,411
I was happy to see them,
but I was like, "Why are they so late?

1712
01:35:59,411 --> 01:36:01,741
What could be that fun?" I thought that.

1713
01:36:01,741 --> 01:36:04,521
- He was bothered.
- My gosh.

1714
01:36:04,521 --> 01:36:07,271
- Aigoo.
- She's looking chipper.

1715
01:36:07,271 --> 01:36:08,861
Where's she going?

1716
01:36:09,861 --> 01:36:12,721
- Can I check out the room?
- Yes, come in.

1717
01:36:12,721 --> 01:36:14,621
It's the same, right?

1718
01:36:14,621 --> 01:36:17,491
- She's in his room now?
- Seong Min is in the bathroom now.

1719
01:36:17,491 --> 01:36:19,721
[Why in that moment?]

1720
01:36:19,721 --> 01:36:22,521
- He can't come out.
- No!

1721
01:36:24,941 --> 01:36:26,411
Do you want vitamins?

1722
01:36:26,411 --> 01:36:28,181
I want vitamins.

1723
01:36:28,181 --> 01:36:31,001
- Take one.
- Really? Thank you.

1724
01:36:31,001 --> 01:36:33,991
Let me know if you need it.
I'll get it for you.

1725
01:36:37,131 --> 01:36:40,071
- Should we eat the Dubai chocolate cookies?
- Yes.

1726
01:36:40,071 --> 01:36:41,691
Hyung, do you want Dubai chocolate cookies?

1727
01:36:41,691 --> 01:36:43,931
- Do you want Dubai chocolate cookies?
- Dubai chocolate cookies?

1728
01:36:43,931 --> 01:36:46,681
Just leave. Why ask him?

1729
01:36:46,681 --> 01:36:49,041
He thought they were leaving.

1730
01:36:49,041 --> 01:36:52,091
- We brought some.
- You bought them?

1731
01:36:52,091 --> 01:36:53,611
How many did you get?

1732
01:36:53,611 --> 01:36:56,231
We got 10.

1733
01:36:56,231 --> 01:36:58,791
- I splurged a bit.
- What are you, a billionaire?

1734
01:36:58,791 --> 01:37:00,741
- Walking around with that bag.
- Is it a designer purse?

1735
01:37:00,741 --> 01:37:02,351
Let's sit on the floor.

1736
01:37:02,351 --> 01:37:04,871
[Showing off the Dubai chocolate cookies]

1737
01:37:04,871 --> 01:37:06,371
We're going all out.

1738
01:37:06,371 --> 01:37:08,621
You're prepping for an operation.

1739
01:37:08,621 --> 01:37:12,411
- Did you wash your hands?
- I washed mine.

1740
01:37:12,411 --> 01:37:13,311
[Laughing]

1741
01:37:13,311 --> 01:37:15,371
- Should we start?
- Yes.

1742
01:37:17,401 --> 01:37:20,041
I hope it's good.

1743
01:37:20,041 --> 01:37:21,191
[Bite]

1744
01:37:21,191 --> 01:37:23,641
Gosh, looks good.

1745
01:37:26,291 --> 01:37:27,721
Is it good?

1746
01:37:27,721 --> 01:37:29,031
[Big bite]

1747
01:37:29,931 --> 01:37:31,511
Wow, this is...

1748
01:37:31,511 --> 01:37:33,601
Does it taste the same?

1749
01:37:33,601 --> 01:37:35,641
It's better.

1750
01:37:35,641 --> 01:37:36,621
[Glancing]

1751
01:37:39,771 --> 01:37:42,611
- Yu Gyeong is on cloud nine today.
- So sweet.

1752
01:37:42,611 --> 01:37:44,731
I can't chew it.

1753
01:37:46,061 --> 01:37:48,511
I keep wiping, but it won't go away.

1754
01:37:48,511 --> 01:37:51,131
[Dubai chocolate cookie tint
that won't come off]

1755
01:37:51,131 --> 01:37:53,901
I got a proper Dubai chocolate lip tint.

1756
01:38:00,541 --> 01:38:03,351
What did you have for dinner?
Dinner or lunch?

1757
01:38:03,351 --> 01:38:06,031
Dinner. We had one meal today.

1758
01:38:06,031 --> 01:38:09,261
We went to a cafe and had dinner.

1759
01:38:09,261 --> 01:38:12,271
You couldn't find the right time.

1760
01:38:12,271 --> 01:38:13,951
He can't hide his feelings.

1761
01:38:13,951 --> 01:38:15,711
Pork jowl...

1762
01:38:15,711 --> 01:38:18,011
With rice and greens.

1763
01:38:19,711 --> 01:38:22,161
How nice. Sounds good.

1764
01:38:23,621 --> 01:38:26,521
It was my first time there.

1765
01:38:26,521 --> 01:38:29,641
It was tasty. We licked the bowls clean.

1766
01:38:29,641 --> 01:38:33,081
He had sent Yu Gyeong a text last night.

1767
01:38:33,081 --> 01:38:34,111
[Glancing]

1768
01:38:34,111 --> 01:38:35,911
They had gambas, too.

1769
01:38:36,781 --> 01:38:39,091
I wanted to chat with Yu Gyeong, but...

1770
01:38:39,091 --> 01:38:41,711
- Perilla seed pasta.
- They sell a lot of tasty stuff.

1771
01:38:41,711 --> 01:38:43,611
They look so close right now.

1772
01:38:43,611 --> 01:38:48,951
I was bothered that
they were already so tight.

1773
01:38:50,581 --> 01:38:53,061
Things keep going wrong.

1774
01:38:56,471 --> 01:38:57,681
[Gyu Ri and Seo Won are home]

1775
01:38:57,681 --> 01:38:58,891
Gyu Ri.

1776
01:38:58,891 --> 01:39:01,771
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1777
01:39:01,771 --> 01:39:03,671
- Shall we?
- Yes.

1778
01:39:06,861 --> 01:39:09,021
This is for real.

1779
01:39:10,251 --> 01:39:11,071
Huh?

1780
01:39:11,071 --> 01:39:13,721
Hello.

1781
01:39:13,721 --> 01:39:16,141
My guess was wrong.

1782
01:39:16,141 --> 01:39:18,241
Huh? Seo Won?

1783
01:39:19,301 --> 01:39:20,221
What?

1784
01:39:20,221 --> 01:39:24,581
- Hello.
- Hello.

1785
01:39:24,581 --> 01:39:27,321
Why are you back so late? I feel hurt.

1786
01:39:27,321 --> 01:39:29,171
What were you doing this late?

1787
01:39:29,171 --> 01:39:30,441
Huh? Soju?

1788
01:39:30,441 --> 01:39:33,881
I'm drinking soju
after waiting all this time.

1789
01:39:33,881 --> 01:39:35,481
Where's Min Ju?

1790
01:39:35,481 --> 01:39:37,511
- She's not back yet.
- Really?

1791
01:39:37,511 --> 01:39:41,161
I thought Seo Won's was the orange...
I keep saying that.

1792
01:39:41,161 --> 01:39:42,641
- Can I see your book?
- Pardon?

1793
01:39:42,641 --> 01:39:44,361
Can I show it to you?

1794
01:39:44,361 --> 01:39:46,641
I'll just look at this.

1795
01:39:47,931 --> 01:39:51,641
This won't reveal his nickname.

1796
01:39:51,641 --> 01:39:53,701
I went after work.

1797
01:39:53,701 --> 01:39:56,741
It was around five, I think?

1798
01:39:56,741 --> 01:39:58,611
Hey, now.

1799
01:39:58,611 --> 01:40:01,381
I went straight there.

1800
01:40:02,131 --> 01:40:03,721
Meeting at seven.

1801
01:40:04,471 --> 01:40:05,791
[Yesterday afternoon]

1802
01:40:05,791 --> 01:40:10,541
I think gray or brown would suit you well.

1803
01:40:10,541 --> 01:40:13,841
I have a brown one, too.
I'll show it to you later.

1804
01:40:13,841 --> 01:40:15,931
The brown sweater.

1805
01:40:20,221 --> 01:40:23,281
- What did you do today?
- Us?

1806
01:40:23,281 --> 01:40:27,041
- We had a Western-style dinner. Steak.
- Must've been tasty.

1807
01:40:27,041 --> 01:40:31,221
[Is it a coincidence that Wu Yeol
is wearing a brown sweater?]

1808
01:40:31,941 --> 01:40:33,561
[Staring]

1809
01:40:33,561 --> 01:40:36,271
[Jaws drop]

1810
01:40:36,271 --> 01:40:37,811
[Shocked]

1811
01:40:37,811 --> 01:40:41,341
She'll hear about him wearing
a brown sweater and...

1812
01:40:41,341 --> 01:40:43,361
[The brown sweater is so meaningful]

1813
01:40:43,361 --> 01:40:45,691
- Were you home alone?
- Yes, I was wondering, "Is this right?"

1814
01:40:45,691 --> 01:40:48,451
When did you two come home?

1815
01:40:48,451 --> 01:40:49,781
When did we come home?

1816
01:40:49,781 --> 01:40:51,591
- 11?
- 11:30?

1817
01:40:51,591 --> 01:40:54,981
- It hasn't been that long.
- No, 11.

1818
01:40:54,981 --> 01:40:58,091
It was 10:30.

1819
01:40:58,091 --> 01:41:01,071
- Why change the time?
- Was it 10:30?

1820
01:41:03,701 --> 01:41:06,581
Yu Gyeong is making that face again.

1821
01:41:06,581 --> 01:41:10,171
What did you do? You two.

1822
01:41:10,171 --> 01:41:12,311
What would you call that place?

1823
01:41:12,311 --> 01:41:14,801
An izakaya?

1824
01:41:14,801 --> 01:41:17,261
Did you drink?

1825
01:41:17,261 --> 01:41:20,371
- Yes. A little. I felt okay.
- You did?

1826
01:41:20,371 --> 01:41:23,141
- What a relief.
- What's with her voice?

1827
01:41:23,141 --> 01:41:26,541
- I felt uncomfortable.
- Why is she so discouraged?

1828
01:41:26,541 --> 01:41:29,691
I didn't want to let it show.

1829
01:41:29,691 --> 01:41:31,821
I was like, "What's the deal?"

1830
01:41:31,821 --> 01:41:34,521
She's asking herself that.

1831
01:41:34,521 --> 01:41:36,791
[Seo Won is back in the room]

1832
01:41:38,471 --> 01:41:40,181
Apple?

1833
01:41:41,111 --> 01:41:44,121
[Just a bite]

1834
01:41:44,121 --> 01:41:45,421
[Laughing]

1835
01:41:47,861 --> 01:41:49,351
[Crunch]

1836
01:41:50,311 --> 01:41:52,401
He's too funny.

1837
01:41:53,811 --> 01:41:56,151
People might get the wrong idea.

1838
01:42:00,201 --> 01:42:03,101
The men are about the same age.

1839
01:42:03,101 --> 01:42:06,071
I ate before going to work today.

1840
01:42:08,641 --> 01:42:13,021
I went to Seongsu and Shinnonhyeon.

1841
01:42:13,021 --> 01:42:16,761
We had risotto, and had a second
round at a snack bar.

1842
01:42:16,761 --> 01:42:17,851
[Bothered]

1843
01:42:19,261 --> 01:42:21,971
Aren't you tired? Are you okay?

1844
01:42:21,971 --> 01:42:24,101
I'm more awake now.

1845
01:42:24,101 --> 01:42:25,641
I'm okay.

1846
01:42:26,501 --> 01:42:28,481
Where did you guys go?

1847
01:42:29,891 --> 01:42:31,481
My neighborhood.

1848
01:42:31,481 --> 01:42:33,261
- Seongsu?
- Konkuk University area.

1849
01:42:33,261 --> 01:42:34,991
Konkuk?

1850
01:42:34,991 --> 01:42:36,591
He's acting so guilty.

1851
01:42:36,591 --> 01:42:39,831
Whenever we made eye contact, I felt...

1852
01:42:41,331 --> 01:42:42,701
a bit guilty.

1853
01:42:42,701 --> 01:42:48,151
There were so many books,
including the ones I read.

1854
01:42:48,151 --> 01:42:51,341
[Wu Yeol is leaving]

1855
01:42:51,341 --> 01:42:53,541
We bought each other books.

1856
01:42:53,541 --> 01:42:56,361
Bookstore date, a meal, and that was it?

1857
01:42:56,361 --> 01:42:59,651
We ate, and she went to Mr. Tree.

1858
01:43:00,651 --> 01:43:02,451
His seat.

1859
01:43:04,051 --> 01:43:07,051
We ate and drank a bit.

1860
01:43:07,051 --> 01:43:09,081
- What?
- Huh? Huh?

1861
01:43:09,081 --> 01:43:11,491
- Don't sit there.
- Hold on.

1862
01:43:11,491 --> 01:43:13,681
[Bothered]

1863
01:43:15,741 --> 01:43:18,271
[Wu Yeol is sitting next to Gyu Ri]

1864
01:43:19,441 --> 01:43:21,401
You bought the jellies, right?

1865
01:43:21,401 --> 01:43:24,041
- You bought them, right?
- These? I did.

1866
01:43:24,041 --> 01:43:27,971
Not these. I bought the old ones.

1867
01:43:27,971 --> 01:43:29,671
[Covering her mouth]

1868
01:43:29,671 --> 01:43:33,521
Come on. Come on.

1869
01:43:33,521 --> 01:43:37,591
- Why is he...
- More misunderstanding.

1870
01:43:37,591 --> 01:43:40,711
We bought them at a store on the way back.

1871
01:43:40,711 --> 01:43:41,961
Together?

1872
01:43:41,961 --> 01:43:43,381
She's having indigestion again.

1873
01:43:43,381 --> 01:43:48,401
[Feeling the tension amidst the conversation]

1874
01:43:48,401 --> 01:43:52,511
I was like, "That author has a new book?"

1875
01:43:53,351 --> 01:43:54,941
[Jun Hyeon and Min Ju arrive last]

1876
01:43:54,941 --> 01:43:56,681
That was good timing.

1877
01:43:56,681 --> 01:44:00,001
- Hello.
- Welcome back.

1878
01:44:00,001 --> 01:44:02,551
- Hi.
- Welcome back.

1879
01:44:02,551 --> 01:44:04,101
What were you up to?

1880
01:44:04,101 --> 01:44:06,281
We were chatting.

1881
01:44:06,281 --> 01:44:08,751
What did you guys do?

1882
01:44:08,751 --> 01:44:12,741
We ate and went to the Han River.

1883
01:44:15,471 --> 01:44:17,101
Did you take a walk there?

1884
01:44:17,101 --> 01:44:19,621
No, we just stayed in the car.

1885
01:44:22,831 --> 01:44:26,471
- The queen... The sitting queen.
- The sitting queen?

1886
01:44:26,471 --> 01:44:29,301
Yes, I was the sitting queen today.

1887
01:44:30,181 --> 01:44:31,541
[Many emotions are intersecting tonight]

1888
01:44:31,541 --> 01:44:33,681
- Gosh.
- So pretty.

1889
01:44:33,681 --> 01:44:37,181
It's snowing. It's actually snowing.

1890
01:44:37,181 --> 01:44:42,241
[Did you detect their heart signals?]

1891
01:44:42,241 --> 01:44:48,911
[Predict the seven people's
love lines based on clues!]

1892
01:44:50,531 --> 01:44:53,061
We didn't. Pass, pass.

1893
01:44:53,061 --> 01:44:55,501
- This is hard.
- It's too hard.

1894
01:44:55,501 --> 01:44:57,621
Let's go with the easy ones first.

1895
01:44:57,621 --> 01:44:58,821
Which one's easy?

1896
01:44:58,821 --> 01:45:00,681
Yu Gyeong. Yu Gyeong. She's easy.

1897
01:45:00,681 --> 01:45:02,721
She's easy?

1898
01:45:02,721 --> 01:45:05,041
- How's she easy?
- She's choosing Wu Yeol tonight.

1899
01:45:05,041 --> 01:45:06,801
Yu Gyeong's pick?

1900
01:45:06,801 --> 01:45:08,181
- Wu Yeol, of course.
- Right?

1901
01:45:08,181 --> 01:45:11,001
Who? This person?

1902
01:45:11,001 --> 01:45:12,881
- Why?
- Are you serious?

1903
01:45:12,881 --> 01:45:16,131
Yu Gyeong fell for him during their date.

1904
01:45:16,131 --> 01:45:19,121
I think she texts any of these three.

1905
01:45:19,121 --> 01:45:21,841
- I'd never text Park Wu Yeol, either.
- This isn't right.

1906
01:45:21,841 --> 01:45:25,031
This is not a joke. Tell them.

1907
01:45:25,031 --> 01:45:28,231
Wu Yeol is the only one,
but think about what he did.

1908
01:45:28,231 --> 01:45:29,801
They came home after the date.

1909
01:45:29,801 --> 01:45:32,261
As soon as she came, he changed his tune.

1910
01:45:32,261 --> 01:45:35,281
When she asked when they got back,
he lied that it was earlier.

1911
01:45:35,281 --> 01:45:37,551
And most importantly,

1912
01:45:37,551 --> 01:45:40,361
he left and came back to switch seats.

1913
01:45:40,361 --> 01:45:42,711
He sat right next to Gyu Ri.

1914
01:45:42,711 --> 01:45:45,141
- Is that okay?
- She obviously got upset.

1915
01:45:45,141 --> 01:45:47,281
Upset enough to change her mind?

1916
01:45:47,281 --> 01:45:49,691
She has to at this point.

1917
01:45:49,691 --> 01:45:51,521
She won't text him out of disdain.

1918
01:45:51,521 --> 01:45:53,741
- Out of disdain.
- No, no.

1919
01:45:53,741 --> 01:45:55,601
In Heart Signal so far,

1920
01:45:55,601 --> 01:45:57,821
we haven't been persuaded by Sang Min.

1921
01:45:57,821 --> 01:46:00,321
- But he was right away.
- He's a good man.

1922
01:46:00,321 --> 01:46:03,101
I really don't get it. How could she...

1923
01:46:03,101 --> 01:46:04,421
But it's still Wu Yeol.

1924
01:46:04,421 --> 01:46:07,031
She won't change her mind because of that.

1925
01:46:07,031 --> 01:46:09,331
Why won't she change her mind?

1926
01:46:09,331 --> 01:46:11,931
Their date was so great.

1927
01:46:11,931 --> 01:46:14,171
Yu Gyeong is too far gone at this point.

1928
01:46:14,171 --> 01:46:16,421
Let's watch it, then. I'll let you do it.

1929
01:46:16,421 --> 01:46:18,681
We'll go with it, but it's wrong.

1930
01:46:18,681 --> 01:46:21,471
If this is correct,

1931
01:46:21,471 --> 01:46:24,941
can you finish ripping your sweater?

1932
01:46:24,941 --> 01:46:27,921
- I'll take it all off.
- Okay, okay.

1933
01:46:27,921 --> 01:46:29,671
Seo Won is easy, isn't he?

1934
01:46:29,671 --> 01:46:31,541
He's Gyu Ri starting today.

1935
01:46:31,541 --> 01:46:32,991
I think it's Gyu Ri today.

1936
01:46:32,991 --> 01:46:34,941
Right. Seo Won is definitely Gyu Ri.

1937
01:46:34,941 --> 01:46:38,701
They normally text their date of the day.

1938
01:46:38,701 --> 01:46:40,921
Right. But knowing Seo Won,

1939
01:46:40,921 --> 01:46:45,721
he has to text Gyu Ri
since they talked so much.

1940
01:46:45,721 --> 01:46:47,991
Seo Won texted Min Ju the day before, right?

1941
01:46:47,991 --> 01:46:51,911
He didn't have anyone.
He found someone finally.

1942
01:46:51,911 --> 01:46:54,841
He flirted with his eyes over drinks.

1943
01:46:54,841 --> 01:46:59,151
He was glancing, thinking, "She's not bad."

1944
01:46:59,151 --> 01:47:00,821
Seo Won chooses Gyu Ri.

1945
01:47:00,821 --> 01:47:03,541
Jun Hyeon chooses Min Ju.

1946
01:47:03,541 --> 01:47:05,971
I agree that he chooses Min Ju.

1947
01:47:05,971 --> 01:47:07,901
- He's clueless.
- He finds everything fun.

1948
01:47:07,901 --> 01:47:09,501
He doesn't stress out. No stress.

1949
01:47:09,501 --> 01:47:12,771
He thinks it was perfect.
He's sleeping well tonight.

1950
01:47:12,771 --> 01:47:15,131
He expressed his feelings to her enough.

1951
01:47:15,131 --> 01:47:17,941
- I can see that.
- It could be.

1952
01:47:17,941 --> 01:47:19,471
That's why Min Ju is hard.

1953
01:47:19,471 --> 01:47:22,401
She went on two dates.
It's Seong Min or Jun Hyeon.

1954
01:47:22,401 --> 01:47:25,001
- She might still be into Seong Min.
- She might,

1955
01:47:25,001 --> 01:47:29,181
but Jun Hyeon's new side affected her, too.

1956
01:47:29,181 --> 01:47:34,271
But in the end, she thought,
"He's not so easy to talk to."

1957
01:47:34,271 --> 01:47:37,191
She said she was shocked
during the interview.

1958
01:47:37,191 --> 01:47:40,091
It was more fun than expected,
but she didn't fall for him.

1959
01:47:40,091 --> 01:47:41,401
Of course not.

1960
01:47:41,401 --> 01:47:44,561
I think she'll still choose Seong Min.

1961
01:47:44,561 --> 01:47:47,211
After what he did yesterday? After all that?

1962
01:47:47,211 --> 01:47:51,531
She noticed that Seong Min
has feelings for Yu Gyeong.

1963
01:47:51,531 --> 01:47:54,241
He obviously has feelings for her.

1964
01:47:54,241 --> 01:47:56,851
Will she still text him?

1965
01:47:56,851 --> 01:48:00,361
Or let's say they're both out.

1966
01:48:00,361 --> 01:48:03,771
She cast a random vote last week.

1967
01:48:03,771 --> 01:48:05,921
Right. She went with the lint roller.

1968
01:48:05,921 --> 01:48:09,571
- She'll choose Seo Won this time.
- I think she might text Wu Yeol again.

1969
01:48:09,571 --> 01:48:11,501
Or another meaningless vote for someone else?

1970
01:48:11,501 --> 01:48:15,341
You can say she lost her mind if she does.

1971
01:48:15,341 --> 01:48:17,671
It's neither Seo Won nor Wu Yeol.

1972
01:48:17,671 --> 01:48:19,951
I don't think
she'll cast a random vote again.

1973
01:48:19,951 --> 01:48:21,181
I think it's Seong Min, then.

1974
01:48:21,181 --> 01:48:23,011
- Should we go with Seong Min?
- Let's do that.

1975
01:48:23,011 --> 01:48:25,291
I don't feel good about this.

1976
01:48:25,291 --> 01:48:27,101
We're right since he's saying that.

1977
01:48:27,101 --> 01:48:29,781
- I don't feel good about this.
- Min Ju and Seong Min.

1978
01:48:29,781 --> 01:48:33,041
You haven't moved on yet? Are you a fool?

1979
01:48:33,041 --> 01:48:37,311
She could like Seong Min more
after meeting Jun Hyeon.

1980
01:48:37,311 --> 01:48:41,231
She might think that,
but she knows he's not...

1981
01:48:41,231 --> 01:48:44,031
Please listen to me. Why don't you listen?

1982
01:48:44,031 --> 01:48:45,961
Why are you ignoring me?

1983
01:48:45,961 --> 01:48:48,521
- Did you say something?
- No, sorry.

1984
01:48:48,521 --> 01:48:50,391
I'll stop talking now.

1985
01:48:50,391 --> 01:48:53,031
- And Kim Seong Min.
- Who does Seong Min choose?

1986
01:48:53,031 --> 01:48:55,841
Will he choose Min Ju or Yu Gyeong?

1987
01:48:55,841 --> 01:48:58,501
I don't know anymore.

1988
01:48:58,501 --> 01:49:00,901
When he was drinking beer alone,

1989
01:49:00,901 --> 01:49:04,341
he was still interested in Yu Gyeong,
but she got close to Wu Yeol first.

1990
01:49:04,341 --> 01:49:06,641
He's still interested in Yu Gyeong.

1991
01:49:06,641 --> 01:49:09,341
But we need to decide
whether he'll message her.

1992
01:49:09,341 --> 01:49:10,531
It's Yu Gyeong.

1993
01:49:10,531 --> 01:49:13,341
Seong Min is a good boy.

1994
01:49:13,341 --> 01:49:16,351
He won't even text Min Ju after the date?

1995
01:49:16,351 --> 01:49:20,531
Being social is as important as love.

1996
01:49:20,531 --> 01:49:25,591
If he chooses Min Ju,
it won't be because of the date.

1997
01:49:25,591 --> 01:49:28,211
He was a bit hurt by their being lovey-dovey.

1998
01:49:28,211 --> 01:49:30,721
He might think, "I can't text her tonight."

1999
01:49:30,721 --> 01:49:32,611
Yes, that's right.

2000
01:49:32,611 --> 01:49:35,081
That might be why he chooses Min Ju.

2001
01:49:35,081 --> 01:49:37,881
- Seong Min chooses Min Ju.
- Let's go with Min Ju.

2002
01:49:37,881 --> 01:49:40,921
We have Gyu Ri and Wu Yeol left.

2003
01:49:40,921 --> 01:49:43,001
- This is hard.
- Wu Yeol is hard.

2004
01:49:43,001 --> 01:49:46,061
Wu Yeol is definitely Yu Gyeong.

2005
01:49:46,061 --> 01:49:50,481
Knowing his sly tendencies, it has to be

2006
01:49:50,481 --> 01:49:52,961
- Yu Gyeong tonight.
- Yu Gyeong.

2007
01:49:52,961 --> 01:49:56,231
- I think it's Gyu Ri.
- I think so, too.

2008
01:49:56,231 --> 01:49:58,921
He was devoted to Jeong Gyu Ri,

2009
01:49:58,921 --> 01:50:02,141
but he now wants
to get to know Yu Gyeong, too.

2010
01:50:02,141 --> 01:50:05,851
Yu Gyeong? That could be.

2011
01:50:05,851 --> 01:50:09,371
After hurting Yu Gyeong's feelings,

2012
01:50:09,371 --> 01:50:11,111
would he still text her?

2013
01:50:11,111 --> 01:50:16,231
- Will he be like, "It was fun today"?
- He wants to be a nice guy.

2014
01:50:16,231 --> 01:50:18,701
- He wants to get to know Yu Gyeong, too.
- I know what you mean.

2015
01:50:18,701 --> 01:50:21,711
He might've changed his mind.

2016
01:50:21,711 --> 01:50:23,131
I think it's Yu Gyeong.

2017
01:50:23,131 --> 01:50:24,931
What did Jjuki tell you?

2018
01:50:24,931 --> 01:50:27,191
It's Tsuki, not Jjuki.

2019
01:50:27,191 --> 01:50:28,361
She's not Jjuki.

2020
01:50:28,361 --> 01:50:32,941
[Slightly mistaken]

2021
01:50:32,941 --> 01:50:36,081
Let's trust Tsuki on this.

2022
01:50:36,081 --> 01:50:38,101
Gyu Ri. Gyu Ri.

2023
01:50:38,101 --> 01:50:41,051
Don't you think Gyu Ri chooses Wu Yeol?

2024
01:50:41,051 --> 01:50:43,551
Tsuki, you're pretty good.

2025
01:50:43,551 --> 01:50:45,981
I think Gyu Ri chooses Wu Yeol.

2026
01:50:45,981 --> 01:50:48,951
She might not if he were
sitting next to Yu Gyeong.

2027
01:50:48,951 --> 01:50:52,361
But he left and sat next to her.

2028
01:50:52,361 --> 01:50:54,511
He won her over by doing that.

2029
01:50:54,511 --> 01:50:56,681
It's 100% Wu Yeol.

2030
01:50:56,681 --> 01:51:00,081
It could've been Seo Won before she got home.

2031
01:51:00,081 --> 01:51:03,071
But when she got home,
Wu Yeol was wearing a brown sweater.

2032
01:51:03,071 --> 01:51:05,761
He wore that sweater,
thinking it would be her.

2033
01:51:05,761 --> 01:51:07,681
So romantic!

2034
01:51:07,681 --> 01:51:11,301
We didn't see it, but he was doing
this when Gyu Ri came home.

2035
01:51:11,301 --> 01:51:13,691
[Look at my brown sweater]

2036
01:51:13,691 --> 01:51:16,351
I think so. I think so.

2037
01:51:16,351 --> 01:51:20,521
Gyu Ri chooses Wu Yeol according to you guys.

2038
01:51:20,521 --> 01:51:24,111
Perfect score. Let's get the perfect score.

2039
01:51:24,111 --> 01:51:25,841
Let's go.

2040
01:51:28,961 --> 01:51:31,421
Oppa, what time do you have to leave?

2041
01:51:31,421 --> 01:51:33,781
Why are you talking to me formally?

2042
01:51:33,781 --> 01:51:36,761
- Can I? What time?
- Of course.

2043
01:51:37,831 --> 01:51:40,671
I have a two-hour-long class.

2044
01:51:40,671 --> 01:51:44,781
- What are you taking to school?
- I think the subway and the bus.

2045
01:51:44,781 --> 01:51:46,601
Do you want a ride?

2046
01:51:46,601 --> 01:51:48,651
I'd love that.

2047
01:51:48,651 --> 01:51:51,961
Leave about 30 minutes early.

2048
01:51:51,961 --> 01:51:53,931
Thirty minutes? Thirty minutes?

2049
01:51:53,931 --> 01:51:56,271
- Leave at nine?
- Got it.

2050
01:51:56,271 --> 01:51:59,881
Huh? Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong are carpooling?

2051
01:51:59,881 --> 01:52:04,271
Why are you showing this now? So unfair.

2052
01:52:05,191 --> 01:52:08,581
- Thank you.
- Don't mention it.

2053
01:52:17,801 --> 01:52:19,901
[Ding]

2054
01:52:22,161 --> 01:52:23,511
You kept the ringer on.

2055
01:52:23,511 --> 01:52:25,591
Well, yes.

2056
01:52:25,591 --> 01:52:27,821
Should I turn mine on, too?

2057
01:52:27,821 --> 01:52:32,441
It's because I keep missing it.

2058
01:52:33,371 --> 01:52:34,861
How fun.

2059
01:52:34,861 --> 01:52:38,081
This weekend was more fun than usual.

2060
01:52:38,081 --> 01:52:42,181
Next week, we'll be like,
"See me on the rooftop."

2061
01:52:42,181 --> 01:52:44,661
There's no need to compete.

2062
01:52:44,661 --> 01:52:46,621
It's not a competition.

2063
01:52:46,621 --> 01:52:48,371
You want to do that, don't you?

2064
01:52:48,371 --> 01:52:51,701
- Are you gearing up for it?
- Vroom, vroom.

2065
01:52:52,581 --> 01:52:55,791
EVs move as soon as you accelerate.

2066
01:52:55,791 --> 01:52:58,071
It's Yellow.

2067
01:52:58,071 --> 01:52:59,631
[My Dog, Yellow: Thanks for tonight!]

2068
01:53:00,351 --> 01:53:04,741
[My Dog, Yellow]

2069
01:53:04,741 --> 01:53:06,231
[Of course, it's Wu Yeol]

2070
01:53:06,231 --> 01:53:08,911
Yu Gyeong was an easy one today.

2071
01:53:08,911 --> 01:53:11,601
You promised to rip your sweater.
What happened?

2072
01:53:11,601 --> 01:53:12,771
Are you changing your mind?

2073
01:53:12,771 --> 01:53:15,801
- You were supposed to rip it.
- Take it off now.

2074
01:53:15,801 --> 01:53:18,821
Let us see your Marine physique.

2075
01:53:18,821 --> 01:53:20,121
[Buzz]

2076
01:53:22,581 --> 01:53:24,491
[Sleepy Bear]

2077
01:53:24,491 --> 01:53:26,541
- Min Ju.
- It's Min Ju.

2078
01:53:26,541 --> 01:53:29,541
Okay, okay. Seong Min. We were right.

2079
01:53:29,541 --> 01:53:31,831
[Sleepy Bear]

2080
01:53:31,831 --> 01:53:33,941
[Glancing]

2081
01:53:40,601 --> 01:53:42,921
Gyu Ri is always thinking.

2082
01:53:44,151 --> 01:53:49,001
[Who does Gyu Ri text?]

2083
01:53:55,391 --> 01:53:59,211
[Dried Sweet Potato: The brown
sweater looks good on you]

2084
01:53:59,771 --> 01:54:04,121
[Dried Sweet Potato]

2085
01:54:04,121 --> 01:54:06,241
Gosh! Oh, well.

2086
01:54:06,981 --> 01:54:08,981
Nice, nice, nice.

2087
01:54:08,981 --> 01:54:12,351
Gyu Ri texted him despite the date.

2088
01:54:15,471 --> 01:54:17,971
I should check my phone.

2089
01:54:22,111 --> 01:54:24,921
[Anticipating]

2090
01:54:28,931 --> 01:54:33,371
[Heart Signal:
All texts have been sent today]

2091
01:54:33,371 --> 01:54:35,901
I gasped like this.

2092
01:54:38,411 --> 01:54:43,151
It was such a nice date.
I thought it was memorable.

2093
01:54:43,151 --> 01:54:45,931
[Disappointed]

2094
01:54:47,631 --> 01:54:53,521
[The feelings
aren't being reciprocated tonight]

2095
01:54:56,681 --> 01:55:01,871
Wu Yeol has been texting me for three days.

2096
01:55:01,871 --> 01:55:04,241
She still doesn't know.

2097
01:55:04,241 --> 01:55:08,441
I was hoping Hamster would text me.

2098
01:55:09,441 --> 01:55:14,281
Who would understand this feeling?

2099
01:55:20,021 --> 01:55:23,341
He's Salt Bread. She still doesn't know.

2100
01:55:23,341 --> 01:55:30,011
[Another person
is waiting for Wu Yeol's text]

2101
01:55:34,251 --> 01:55:40,891
[Will he approach her as much as
she approached him?]

2102
01:55:40,891 --> 01:55:42,961
She texted him to check his feelings.

2103
01:55:42,961 --> 01:55:46,291
She showed her hand first tonight.

2104
01:55:48,401 --> 01:55:51,361
[Beluga of the Forest: I hope you're happy]

2105
01:55:51,361 --> 01:55:54,051
Beluga. It's Jun Hyeon.

2106
01:55:54,051 --> 01:55:57,301
[Beluga of the Forest]

2107
01:55:57,301 --> 01:55:59,551
Yes, easy. That was easy.

2108
01:55:59,551 --> 01:56:03,331
Jun Hyeon had a great day today.

2109
01:56:09,501 --> 01:56:10,561
[Busy Hamster]

2110
01:56:10,561 --> 01:56:12,081
- Hamster is...
- Seong Min.

2111
01:56:12,081 --> 01:56:14,091
[I had fun thanks to you!
Get some rest and feel better tomorrow]

2112
01:56:14,091 --> 01:56:18,631
[Busy Hamster]

2113
01:56:18,631 --> 01:56:20,701
- Good boy.
- Good boy.

2114
01:56:20,701 --> 01:56:22,801
He's a good boy today.

2115
01:56:22,801 --> 01:56:25,291
We guessed correctly.

2116
01:56:28,271 --> 01:56:30,891
She's feeling happy right away.

2117
01:56:39,941 --> 01:56:41,571
[Buzz]

2118
01:56:43,671 --> 01:56:45,331
[Tired Camel: It's snowing]

2119
01:56:45,331 --> 01:56:46,981
- Camel.
- "It's snowing."

2120
01:56:46,981 --> 01:56:48,381
That's a new nickname.

2121
01:56:48,381 --> 01:56:51,681
[Tired Camel]

2122
01:56:51,681 --> 01:56:53,531
Seo Won obviously chose Gyu Ri.

2123
01:56:53,531 --> 01:56:55,651
We've guessed everything correctly.

2124
01:56:55,651 --> 01:56:58,651
She got Camel's text, but she's not happy.

2125
01:56:58,651 --> 01:57:01,171
- Of course not.
- Because she didn't text him.

2126
01:57:01,171 --> 01:57:02,931
What will Gyu Ri do?

2127
01:57:02,931 --> 01:57:04,681
Okay, Park Wu Yeol.

2128
01:57:04,681 --> 01:57:06,921
Hold on.

2129
01:57:06,921 --> 01:57:10,281
Text Kang Yu Gyeong.
That's why you sat next to Gyu Ri.

2130
01:57:10,281 --> 01:57:21,191
[Who did Wu Yeol text tonight?]

2131
01:57:31,911 --> 01:57:33,661
[Salt Bread: I had fun with you. Good night.]

2132
01:57:33,661 --> 01:57:35,371
- That's right.
- It was Yu Gyeong.

2133
01:57:35,371 --> 01:57:37,451
Good. We're good now.

2134
01:57:37,451 --> 01:57:40,081
[Salt Bread]

2135
01:57:40,081 --> 01:57:44,651
[Pause]

2136
01:57:44,651 --> 01:57:48,661
[She's just realizing Salt Bread is Wu Yeol]

2137
01:57:48,661 --> 01:57:51,861
The struggle begins now for Yu Gyeong.

2138
01:57:51,861 --> 01:57:54,241
[Plop]

2139
01:57:56,481 --> 01:57:58,581
[Laughing]

2140
01:58:10,281 --> 01:58:16,611
[She got his text,
but she's not exactly happy]

2141
01:58:25,111 --> 01:58:26,981
She's in trouble.

2142
01:58:26,981 --> 01:58:30,571
She noticed Gyu Ri and Wu Yeol flirting,

2143
01:58:30,571 --> 01:58:34,271
but she thought they were more solid.

2144
01:58:34,271 --> 01:58:36,821
She thought,
"He's been texting me every night."

2145
01:58:36,821 --> 01:58:40,091
And that's gone now. It must be tough.

2146
01:58:40,091 --> 01:58:44,021
She'd be like, "Did he text me
because of the date?"

2147
01:58:44,021 --> 01:58:48,421
She'd be like,
"Was I mistaken about everything?"

2148
01:58:48,421 --> 01:58:51,241
She'll get confused.
Gyu Ri is in the same boat, too.

2149
01:58:51,241 --> 01:58:53,221
That's why he sat next to her.

2150
01:58:53,221 --> 01:58:54,971
Because he won't be texting her, right?

2151
01:58:54,971 --> 01:58:57,341
How does Gyu Ri feel after
being ignored by Salt Bread?

2152
01:58:57,341 --> 01:59:00,041
At least with this, Gyu Ri...

2153
01:59:00,041 --> 01:59:03,601
She had a date, but she texted him.

2154
01:59:03,601 --> 01:59:05,941
It's like she's in love with him now.

2155
01:59:05,941 --> 01:59:07,481
She must've been afraid of this.

2156
01:59:07,481 --> 01:59:09,811
Only she's getting hurt.

2157
01:59:09,811 --> 01:59:13,821
Wu Yeol appeared
to be leaving both options open.

2158
01:59:13,821 --> 01:59:17,851
He got attention
from both Gyu Ri and Yu Gyeong,

2159
01:59:17,851 --> 01:59:21,271
but they both know about his decision now.

2160
01:59:21,271 --> 01:59:24,271
- He might lose both.
- Things might change tomorrow.

2161
01:59:24,271 --> 01:59:26,461
It will be like, "Wu Yeol has someone else."

2162
01:59:26,461 --> 01:59:29,511
It means he's been texting someone else.

2163
01:59:29,511 --> 01:59:32,441
- She knows that now.
- "It must've been Gyu Ri."

2164
01:59:32,441 --> 01:59:34,251
She'll start thinking about his past moves.

2165
01:59:34,251 --> 01:59:36,401
It's falling apart.

2166
01:59:36,401 --> 01:59:39,681
- What he did to me today was...
- She'll start thinking.

2167
01:59:39,681 --> 01:59:43,181
Both women are knee deep in.

2168
01:59:43,181 --> 01:59:44,751
They're both this deep in.

2169
01:59:44,751 --> 01:59:46,781
They can barely breathe.

2170
01:59:46,781 --> 01:59:49,541
I think Wu Yeol will have
a hard time in the future.

2171
01:59:49,541 --> 01:59:51,981
He has to. Let's be fair.

2172
01:59:51,981 --> 01:59:55,011
[She's too into it again]

2173
01:59:55,011 --> 01:59:58,291
The real drama will start.

2174
01:59:58,291 --> 02:00:00,811
Look how cute the four of them are.

2175
02:00:00,811 --> 02:00:02,381
- Seriously.
- So cute.

2176
02:00:02,381 --> 02:00:04,851
We should photograph them like this.

2177
02:00:04,851 --> 02:00:06,541
So pretty.

2178
02:00:08,011 --> 02:00:09,841
Should I skip work today?

2179
02:00:09,841 --> 02:00:11,681
Should I not go?

2180
02:00:13,411 --> 02:00:15,531
Gosh, why...

2181
02:00:18,141 --> 02:00:19,531
Should we watch a movie this week?

2182
02:00:19,531 --> 02:00:21,911
See a musical, too. So much to do.

2183
02:00:21,911 --> 02:00:24,601
Am I too biased right now?

2184
02:00:26,441 --> 02:00:28,831
Ta-da!

2185
02:00:28,831 --> 02:00:31,331
This is a date. We're only missing two.

2186
02:00:31,331 --> 02:00:33,201
Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri.

2187
02:00:33,201 --> 02:00:35,801
- Hello.
- I think she's here.

2188
02:00:41,041 --> 02:00:42,691
- Did you have a good time?
- Yes.

2189
02:00:42,691 --> 02:00:44,481
I kept waiting.

2190
02:00:48,131 --> 02:00:49,791
- What did you do?
- What did I do?

2191
02:00:49,791 --> 02:00:51,531
I was so worried.

2192
02:00:51,531 --> 02:00:54,431
- Will you go to bed?
- Yes, I'm okay.

2193
02:00:55,241 --> 02:00:58,241
Seriously. Why is it so hard?

2194
02:00:58,241 --> 02:01:00,731
I didn't have dinner.

2195
02:01:11,721 --> 02:01:13,751
Hello. Hello.

2196
02:01:13,751 --> 02:01:15,601
Hello.

2197
02:01:15,601 --> 02:01:18,641
This place is totally unpredictable.
